comments: ["At the start I set it up for a new pup, general obedience, potty training & got signed up for impulse control? How does that make sense. You're introducing a clicker immediately which I find an advanced training method & can very easily be done incorrectly especially because it was not properly explained how it's done. Price is off the charts. In person courses are cheaper. ONLY 7D FREE! Not saying it's a bad app but it's overloaded and inconvenient for first timers or quick exercises & ..money", "The interface is friendly but the dowside is that you cannot try any of the exercises without the 7 days trial or paying for it. I understand that financial support is needed, but people would be more likely to pay for the app if they had a few exercises to try. Even if there is that 7 days trial I don't want to put my card information until I'm sure I want to pay fully for it üòÅ", 'It looks promising but the fact that you can\'t start any of the classes without signing up for the trial is ridiculous Edit for the developer: I don\'t care that you CAN pay for the app. I would just like to see what I\'m signing up for beforehand. If you can\'t get to your "free" version without going THROUGH your paid version then what the hell is the point? Just make it paid and call it a day.', "This app is fantastic. Easily worth the money. My old girl is picking up new tricks and behaviours with ease! It's stimulating for her and she loves our sessions. Highly recommend! It teaches us humans how to teach our pups with step by step instructions, videos and feedback!", "OMG, what is the point of pretending this is anything but a subscription app, any and everything is locked out unless you subscribe. And even when you click continue for free, it's to subscribe to the trial, of your confidence is this small for free users, why would anyone actually use the paid for version? Just switch to a $40 purchase model. There's nothing to try if you're seeing what the app is like before purchase.", 'New puppy. I love the instructions which are clear concise and very helpful so far. This is day one. I will revisit this rating in order to provide a more thorough rating. Day 4 and I am finding Dogo to be absolutely fantastic. Day 29- my puppy and I are making tremendous strides in training. Again the feedback from the trainers is incredibly helpful. My friend and I are getting so much closer as a team.', "It's my favorite dog training app my puppy instantly learned how to sit It's very good to train your dog it's easy I really love this overall,I rate this a 5 star rating, it's the best app in the world. and also add some features to it, I'll really appreciate it notice this, there's no ads but can you make everything cheaper I can't get a new dog.", "I have my 5 month old collie and 8 year old Jack Russell training at the same time at different levels of obedience. Video tutorials are easy to follow and straightforward. I have subscribed to access the full content, which is fair enough. It is good training advice, and I can understand needing to pay for it. At ¬£5.99 a month, you can use it 24/7, and another member of your household can download it and access the account. It's still cheaper than hiring a professional trainer.", "Confusing and too many pop ads for premium. I'm fostering a 15 month old Anatolian Shepherd and he's quite head strong. He was partially trained but there are things we need to work on. Anytime I go to start a lesson an ad pops up and I get sent back to the first page. I can't open the lesson. Very frustrating.", "App works great. Unfortunately the new update on June 21st has changed the UI for the calendar section to track things like wees and poos and it's terrible compared to the old design. It's so much harder to read at a glance and the whole days schedule no longer fits on one screen. Please go back to the old design without the stupid poo emojis or I am probs gonna can em my sub.", "I've never trained a dog and this app really truly does assist me. Amongst the basics, my pup can learn some fun tricks as well! I was skeptical at first especially that you have to pay for service, but I don't mind it all! You'd spend way more paying for obedience school", 'Directions are clear. You can\'t skip exercises that are already mastered. While the exercises aren\'t required to be done in a certain order, the next level are locked until the base is "completed". Different programs feature the same modules, but the modules aren\'t connected so the same exercise must be "taught" twice or more. Circles back to locked variations. Reminders are "on/off" not "set time" so it goes off at 10pm when I\'m in bed.', 'I cannot rate this app high enough, 5++ stars. Everything you need to train your dog at any age. The exercises have worked so well and my dog is learning quickly, much credit goes to the trainers who wrote the training manual and the feedback they give. This app has worked so well to teach me how to train my dog, the features really help me to tain my dog consistently throughout the day. Me and my pet are learning together with Dogo. Cannot recommend enough, get this app!', 'Can\'t change time to am/pm format in calendar. I hope this reaches the developers: most of us do not like to use 24 hour time format in the United States. So the calendar is annoying where we can\'t change that: makes me so some mental calculations every time I use it. Please add in the ability to change to am/pm (12 hr) format. Also: why is there an option for "wake up" but not for "went to sleep" or "bedtime"?', "This is a good app, especially as a first time dog owner. There are some improvements that could be made. The rating system for a lesson should match the lesson rather then just being generic because it doesn't always work e.g. on the puppy biting course, would be great if it was specific to puppy biting so I really know what behaviour I am looking for.", 'Works out well. I just did not understand how this program works so I went in and started the first exercise. Was a bit of a mess so I did it a few times over 2 days and than went in and looked at the next exercise. Which told me to do the first for longer now. Well I was way over that already. Now I know to just go in and do the next exercise without going on on my own. Sit and stay was no problem. One more thing...I am training the dog alone so I have no one to film me doing the exercise üôÉ', "So far so good. I wish they had a button for the calendar when he doesn't pee when I take him out so that the reminder resets. It doesn't reset unless you put if he peed in place or had an accident.", "This app is not free like it says. Yes, they offer a 7 day free trial, but you have to put in all your banking information, and then yeah, you can cancel it after 7 days, but they still. Have your banking information!!! It also takes more than 7 days to know if the training that you're getting from the app is actually working for your dog.", 'Great information! Our first dog is trained very well, very focused and motivated. He\'s an agility "athlete"! Now we\'re using this same guidance to train our second corgi! Highly recommend starting your relationship with your dog with these guidelines! Almost gave 4* because the app layout can seem a bit convoluted.', "It was supposed to be free, but you need to buy a subscription to do ANYTHING in this app. Overall, I thing it would be a good app if you'd just mention that you need to buy the subscription with 7 days free trial.", "The app is really good, I love the family feature but I wish we could post pictures when it comes to the updates and appointments, for example when you put something about a vet visit you could take a picture of the dog at the vets office, or if it's a note for training to take a picture how well it's going, so all the family can see the growth progress as well as reading it", "Pretty great app so far, but I wish there was an option to skip certain lessons or skills. For example I don't see the need for the skill Touch and I want to skip it but I can't.", "I like the app and that it is set up with daily exercises . However I am doing the impulse control class and the exercises are random. I am on day 4 and it is having us do a down w30 sec stay ( down 3), but it hasn't even taught down yet. It's not teaching the basics and building, it's is generating 3 random exercises from the set of 17. I would like to keep the model of dailey exercises and games and have it build from intro to expert.", 'Love it so far, very straight forward set up, everything is easy to find and I love the informative videos demonstrating each task. Love it!', "If I install one more app, that isnt free. Is it so hard to quickly state in the ad that it's a monthly fee to use the app? Now, I'm not clicking on any more apps. They all cost. And the ones that's free are probably so crusty. Lol!", 'So far brilliant app. Explains a lot of reasons why we should do each little task. It has a purpose behind it. My puppy is 9 weeks old and has mastered sit already with this. I think he enjoys the attention he gets too with it. Definitely worth it.', "This app is actually helping me to train my dog. She's a stubborn bulldog/pit. After using doggo, I've noticed that she walks with a loose leash more frequently, and I can actually get her to sit patiently while I pour her food. Consistency is key. If you don't use the app, you'll be wasting your money. However, I'm genuinely surprised by how fast I got these results.", "It's mostly really good and I appreciate the simple straight forward directions and bite size chunks. - As mentioned by others the clicker is a good idea but in practice is hard to use while also holding treats and a lead. I bought a physical clicker almost straight away. - It's really hard to record training that you didn't use the app for. Eg. If I do some sit and stay training without starting the timer I can't then go back and record that without just like running out the timer afterward.", 'I like this app. It has forced me to see training in a different way and has worked wonders for our 7 month old husky. My only complaint is they need tutorials for what to do if your dog does poorly at a specific exercise. Instead you select how well they did and even if they did poorly they say "job well done" and move on. You can message them but it takes a while to hear back. Add a "how to adjust if they aren\'t understanding" feature and it would easily be 5 stars.', "I was giving up hope but this app makes things seem so simple, and where we've hit a hurdle the additional advice is spot on. I love the real trainer feedback.", "Only used it once or twice so far so good. I do like that the clicker is on the phone sonic I can't find mine or don't have it on me I can be consistent.", "This is not a free app. Once all set up I can't add the first potty time without a road block of starting a free trial or paying", "Fantastic app, highly recommended I am so glad I found this app, me and my family are training our puppy and it's great we can do it together on the same app, and even have the older dog on there to learn new stuff and be included. A year's subscription is great value and the dog trainers are really quick to respond to your videos and questions. Thanks team Dogo!", 'Would be a great app if able to pay for subscription. All training and lesson plans and command instructions are locked behind a pay wall. There is however a clicker and whistle available for use!', 'This is a great way to stay on top of progression and give good simple feedback. Wish there was a bit more repetition in the programs, where is the dog doesnt get 4 or 5 stars the exercise should repeat instead of continuing to progress. That being said the feedback and general build is great, awesome price too', "Ive only explored / used the app a couple times, but I like it. I just hate that so much content requires subscription and the cost is a bit high imo. I get app and content makers need revenue and I would consider $20/yr, but I'm not gonna pay $40/year to obtain guidance and info that can be found elsewhere online for free w/ a simple search. Perhaps I'm too cheap, but they should offer tiers of service for ppl who want access to all prewritten material w/o any personalized attention.", 'Very good app. Working my way through with my one year old and having a lot if fun. Looking through the exercises though I think a lot are at a novice level so before the subscription is up you would have completed them all. Having intermediary and advanced levels available would increase customer retention.', "It's unbearably detailed I wish I can have a feline version. This will help me in the long run of allowing both feline and canine to get along. When I'm done and alone.", "Well so far I am loving the Doggo app. I'm just using the basic one and not the premium. The basic one seems to have everything I need to help me train my dog. You pick the exercise or activity you want to do with your dog and it shows you step-by-step on how to do it with examples from other pet parents in short videos. It has a 2 minute countdown timer to do each training and also has a clicker and a whistle in the app. It makes training easier and fun for all.", 'A Stellar Dogo App Experience - Highly Recommended! The user-friendly interface and intuitive design make navigating the app a breeze. From the moment I downloaded it, I was pleasantly surprised by the seamless experience it provides. The app is organized in a logical and easy-to-follow manner, ensuring that I can quickly access the information I need.']

title: Dog Hotel Tycoon
description:
Become a dog hotel tycoon, and create a world for your dog guests to enjoy!

CREATE A WORLD FOR YOUR DOG GUESTS TO ENJOY!
Start with a small dog hotel in a suburban area, and improve it to become the first 5+ star dog hotel! Create areas for your dogs to take naps, eat delicious snacks, play with each other, swim, excercise and much more! Anything to ensure the satisfaction of your dog guests!

WELCOME DOGS FROM ALL AROUND THE WORLD!
Become a dog hotel tycoon and accept more breeds as you grow your hotel, such as Corgi, Dachshund, Pug, Samoyed, Poodle, German Shepherd, Labrador, French Bulldog, English Bulldog, Basset Hound, Chiuahua, Chow Chow, Beagles, Shiba Inu, and many more. Each and every single dog will have their own unique character, behavior, wants and needs; and it is up to you to satisfy them!

TAKE YOUR DOGS TO DAILY DOG EVENTS!
Each day, you'll be able to take your dogs to the daily Dog Show, which is a physical obstacle challenge that will test the health & fitness of your dogs! 
There will also be a new Dog Quiz waiting for you each day, which will test your knowledge about dogs as well as teaching you interesting facts about them!

FEATURES
‚òÖ Easy to play game for every animal lover!
‚òÖ Cute Dogs with unique characteristics and lifelike behavior!
‚òÖ More than 80 dogs to have as guests, and more to come!
‚òÖ Fun rooms and items for your dogs to enjoy!
‚òÖ Send your dogs to Dog Shows!
‚òÖ Learn about dogs and earn rewards with the daily Dog Quiz!

If you love dogs, and incremental idle clicker games, you will love idle Dog Hotel Tycoon. As with all idle clicker games, you will never run out of things to do!

This game is free to play, but it contains items that can be purchased for real money. If you are having any issues with the game or have any feedback, you can always reach us at support@filgames.com
summary: Become a dog hotel tycoon, and create a world for your dog guests to enjoy!

title: Old Friends Dog Game
description:
Welcome to Old Friends Dog Game, where love never grows old! Create your own dog sanctuary in this heartwarming pet rescue simulator. Rescue adorable senior dogs and uncover their life story as you shower them with love. Decorate with cute doggy decor, bake scrumptious dog snacks, and experience the joy of helping cute senior dogs live out their golden years in the best way possible. 

Inspired by the real life pet residents at Old Friends Senior Dog Sanctuary, these cute dogs have heartwarming stories and personalities that you'll uncover as you rescue them and provide the care they need to live their best dog life!

Awarded Gold winner at the 2022 NYX Awards, a finalist for Pocket Gamer's Game of the Year, and a Webby honoree for Social Impact in Games, this cute dog simulator is a must-play!

Gameplay:

‚ù§Ô∏è Meet the town residents and rescue cute senior dogs. Help them live their best life by fulfilling their needs and ensuring their happiness. As you feed, pet, and play with your dogs, their love and loyalty grows.

üìò Choose how the story unfolds. In this dog simulator, you pick the path for each dog's story! Unlock multiple chapters for every cute doggy you rescue.

üíí Customize your dog sanctuary and make it a haven for your dogs. Decorate indoors and outdoors with cute doggy decor that will make your dogs feel right at home!

üßÅ Bake lip-smacking treats for your beloved dogs, ensuring they never go hungry.

üß£ Dress up your dogs in cute pet outfits! Each dog has adorable accessories that you can earn.

üêï Give your dog sanctuary the personal touch - feature a custom profile, a unique avatar, and a gallery of cute photos of each dog!

**********

Old Friends Dog Game is developed and published by Runaway.

This game is free to play but does contain some items available to purchase for real money. If you run into any issues while playing or you have any suggestions, please reach out to us at support@runaway.zendesk.com. OLD FRIENDS DOG SANCTUARY‚Ñ¢ is made by Runaway Play.

comments: ["Absolutely loving the game so far! I'm relieved it's not another match 3 or merge 2 games, and really is about taking care of old dogs and managing the sanctuary. I've seen the game's advert for a long time, I regret not playing it sooner. But better now than never I guess! Only thing is the game keeps crashing on me occasionally while loading a new scene (ex; getting a new dog, loading livestream, .etc) I love the game and I want to support the funding, I'd appreciate a smoother experience. :')", "I played the game a while ago and recently reinstalled it, but now it won't even let me past level one. Everytime I try to stream it just makes the screen go black, and nothing happens. I've tried everything to fix it, reinstalling again, restarting my phone, even went online to try and find an answer. Love the game, just wish I could get further with it.", "I absolutely love this game! It's adorable, and I haven't experienced any bugs (I have played for about a month now). Though, for the Dog Blog, there are limited color options, which, as someone with bright green hair, is a little saddening :( Aside from my dramatics about hair color, I recommend everyone give this game a try! It's so customized, and each dog has their own favorite treats and toys, which is so fun to memorize. I love this game!!", "This game is really amazing and I love the style so much! I really like the game because it's supporting a real life senior dog sanctuary too! But last 3 or 4 days I couldn't get in the game because i got a message about some kind of error and I tried everything to get rid of it but it hasn't been working so far. I got pretty good progress there so it's going to be sad if i lose it. I don't know if its a game error or its like that for someone too but I hope it gets fixed soon!", "Very Cute very relaxing it's really wholesome too! But, I've been having issues lately When I stream the screen becomes black and the music keeps playing and I can't go to the next level because my first time of streaming is glitching I've been having Issues with that so whatever you could do please Fix it....", "First things first, this is not a game you will play for an hour straight. More like a few minutes at a time. Gameplay is fun though. Little thing I mentioned pre-edit, So basically my progress reset, (It has been fixed now.) Devs should probably look into what caused that. Also I don't know if the message I sent to tell them it was fixed worked? All in all, great game, great devs. (What caused the game to reset though?)", "A awesome friendly game where you get to experience adventures and journey with these adorable dogs and the amazing artwork! I love this game. It's just heartwarming. And there is so much more potential to expand apon! The fact that it was based on real dogs and experiences is also amazing. You get to read snippets of real-world inspiration the further you progress.", "This is THE BEST chill/idle kind of game I've ever played. There's so much to do! You are always getting rewards constantly, even past the early game. There are only ads very rarely, when you want to increase your rewards. The dogs are so sweet and have personality that you uncover through their individual story lines. You'll fall in love. I had this game ages ago and left it like I always do with mobile games (I'm fickle lol) and this is the ONLY game I missed so much I had to come back again!", "This game is fun but I got stuck on the streaming stage Everytime I tried the screen would go black to the point I just left and rejoin the game and when I kept trying it took my stuff but never worked if u could see if it's a bug please update Soo it doesn't happen to other people", "it was almost an amazing game, except for the fact that it was lacking in furniture and decoration aspects. it's fun caring for the dogs, but i wish i could put more furnitures. there's so many furniture blueprints, but i cant craft becuz the materials for good furnitures are so hard to get. i wish we could buy materials from donations, or we could get from streams. idk. im quite unsatisfied witht the reward rn", "This make me cry so much. I love idle games. I love that this is based off an actual doggy sanctuary with the actual doggies and with pictures of the actual doggies attached. I'm sad and happy and my heart melt. Some lags and bugs are experienced and the game crashes too. But i just love the concept of this game. Good strategy to make ppl adopt senior dogs and cry cause they're gone too soon", "It's really great especially for dog lovers! I Love it a lot and especially that it's also a real sanctuary.. It really makes me wanna donate now :( but my parents do not allow me sadly... I hope some people will still donate :) definitely will recommend some friends to play this..!", "Old friends dog adventure is such a fun game where you care for older dogs and play the challenges! You get to choose what to say and there's even a dog blog! Definitely would recommend.", 'Sancuaty names could be more customizable(wanted to name mine after my old pup, Timber.) But otherwise, The game is amazing. The graphics are great. The dogs are adorable. And I love the hat for Mack.', 'Absolutely what I was looking for in a game, perfect with little to no ads and with very reasonable microtransactions! Would recommend', "Very cute! I would love if the game would emphasize the importance of identifying dog-friendly costumes that won't bother dogs vs coatumes that will make them uncomfortable all day, but overall its super fun üëç", "THIS GAME IS THE ACTUAL BEST! BAGEL IS SO CUTE MACK IS SO CUTE AND LEO IS SO CUTE,there's so many things to do!Decorate your sanctuary,collect new dogs,and it's all so much fun I love the theme and design of the game and how they're based on real life senior dogs!I wish I could meet them in real life!I was quite sad when I found out they only sold the merchandise in USD cuz I'm from the UK but seriously if I could I'd give this game a million bigillion stars out of a million biggilion stars!‚òÜ", "I am only on 3rd level, and I think it is really fun, cute, and great for a dog lover. I do find it a bit repetitive, but that will probably change over time. I olso do think Runaway's other games are really good too. If you delete their games, your progress will not be saved, though.", 'This game is so cute and entertaining! The dogs are adorable. Even the situations where almost nothing is going on it is really fun. Just baking food or cleaning the house just makes you feel happy and calm. I love this game and I really recommend this game for all dog lovers! ‚ù§Ô∏è', "It's such a cute game about dogs and don't love a dog for its age love it forever no matter what because old dogs are cute too and in the game you can unlock cute dogs like mack and bagel and Leo there so adorable doesn't matter how old a dog is love lasts for eternity I love Leo Babs and Captain Ron too runaway pls update maybe fix the bugs? Not asking for much ty the bug is it takes a bit to load and sometimes when I try saving a picture it says contact support game kicks me out any way to fix", 'I feel good playing with old friends, . I recently had to start a new game over because old friends got accidentally erased , I was devastated. Old friends helps me cope with losing my old friend scrappy. He was my everything, he passed away not long ago he was 16 and so loved. Thank you old friends for reaching out and I was very excited to hear from you. Thank you old friends.', 'This Is such a heartwarming game, I love how simple are the interactions with the dogs. I love the little stories that they include of the dogs adapting to their new home. Amazing game!', 'This game is just so adorable, and the fact that it is based on real life dogs just makes it 10 times more interesting and unique! Love it, keep up the great work. ( I also totally recommend!)', 'This game is adorable and I love the concept of it. It is so cute and so fun, and i love that the dogs each have the personalities of the real pups. And favorite treats and toys. Babs is my favorite pupbso far hehe Ten stars from me!', 'Ohh, they have fixed the problem, the game is really wonderful, and very innovative, please I recommend you download it and give it a try', "So far, it's a really fun game! However I wish furniture was cheaper and there were more coupon codes. But overall, it's really good!", 'I love this game but my account got restarted and when i just wanted to play i was in the start again i dont know to get my stuff and my progress back please help i dont wanna start again.I still have the furniture that is needed coupons. But the ones i crafted is gone and the progress of the dogs are gone and i only have mack again', 'Edit: After 2 years of playing this game, it has become quite dull. The events are all repeats from the years prior... I already have all the rewards from the bake-offs, so why even participate? I have been at the max level for probably a year now. Not much to do after completing the stories. I have 3 senior rescues myself (2 dogs and 1 cat), so this game is perfect for me. I recently applied to vet school and want to focus on old animals. This game is everything I want out of life!!!', 'One of the first times a mobile game has truly felt like a game. Love oozes from every millimeter of this experience. Even the ads are non-intrusive, and from what I understand completely optional. Highly recommend!', 'Game has reset on me twice, erasing all my progress. The first time I used recover to get back to my original game. The second time it reset, I tried to recover my original game, but only the two previous reset games appear, making me start with zero progress. If this is not fixed, I will never play this again.', "Super cute and makes me feel better about playing mind-numbing games that get me nowhere. The only complaint I have is that the app randomly restarts sometimes after an ad video. Also, videos have been unavailable for me all day so I can't get Mack his chicken flavoring ü•π", "Love the premise behind the game and was enjoying playing it. The dog message requests bugged out with no images and did nothing when I clicked on them so I rebooted the game and it lost all my data :( I'm scared it will happen again.", 'This game is so much fun, and although you have to work very hard, the dogs are soo cute. Most relaxing game ever!', "It is amazing there's lots of adventures the dogs are so cute but the best thing is getting more of the dog's stories.", "This is a cute game and I enjoy it but I can't progress past the streaming part as the screen just goes black.", 'So far this is super cute and fun. a little bit slow, but really heartwarming and relaxing.', "Cute little game. I haven't closed it since download because I'm mildly afraid of missing things when my attention differs, but that's the only issue and isn't even really one! The whole app is so fun and adorable that I can't keep my hands off of it üôà", "I don't know why it's taken me so many years to download a wholesome game about dogs. So far into the game, it's easy to follow, lovely story and beautiful graphics. If you love dogs and want causal gameplay, this should suit you:)", "Love this game; it's so nice and wholesome! There has been issues with my progress resetting, but whenever that happens I breeze through the intro sequence then contact support through the game's settings, and they fix it in like a day. One thing I really wish the game had though is the ability to replay cutscenes, because the stories are just really cute.", 'Amazing game 10/10 never run iut of things to do, great asthetics, you just get to chill with good puppers, no annoying ads without consent and great atmosphere, highly recommend']

title: Dog Evolution: Idle Merge Game
description:
If you‚Äôre a dog person and think you know everything about man‚Äôs best friend, your world is about to be rocked! Mix puppy breeds like you‚Äôve never seen before and discover a whole new canine dimension that will leave you barking in such awe: the possibilities are much wow!

Dachshunds, beagles, corgies and retrievers are so last week. Evolved dogs should have an extra eye or two so they can watch over their human friends more efficiently, or a handy horn just in case they get into the odd bar skirmish with a mutant unicorn. It‚Äôs your duty to let the dogs out and help them evolve!

DOGE FEATURES
‚Ä¢ Pantheon: a new place for supreme beings to look down on us mortals and laugh at our misery
‚Ä¢ Impostors: watch out for impostors trying to steal the spotlight from the puppies

HOW TO PLAY
‚Ä¢ Drag and drop similar puppies to create new mysterious doges
‚Ä¢ Use dog eggs to earn coins, buy new creatures and make even more money
‚Ä¢ Alternatively, fiercely tap a rabbit to make coins pop from their eggs

HIGHLIGHTS
‚Ä¢ Different stages and many dog species to discover
‚Ä¢ A mind-blowing story with surprising twists
‚Ä¢ The unexpected mix of creature evolution dynamics and incremental clicker games
‚Ä¢ Doodle-like illustrations
‚Ä¢ Various possible endings: find your destiny
‚Ä¢ No dogs were harmed in the making of this game, only developers

The dog days have just begun! Much fun such wow!

Please note! This game is free to play, but it contains items that can be purchased for real money. Some features and extras mentioned in the description may also have to be purchased for real money.
summary: Combine mutant dog breeds and find out just how wacky puppies can get!

comments: ['Pretty fun, just a bit repetitive but I love it', "I enjoy the app it's cute and it's nice to pass the time, but it's kind of difficult to play a game and genuinely enjoy it when it crashes every single time you play an ad unwillingly. I'll just be in the middle of tapping my dogs and then an ad will play and crash the entire app so I have to reopen it every single time an ad plays Please fix this problem", "I love this game!!!!! its so addicting! who ever is reading this,you should get the game. I've been playing for hours. And it is helpful when your on the go or having no wifi,you cam still play the amazing app!!!! I never really got any ads. the only time i had a ad is when i tried getting more diamond diamonds.", "It's really fun and addicting. I could play for hours and hours, maybe even days. The genius who made this game blows my mind. I can't wait to download more games like this fantastic one. I only have had this game for a little, but I already üíó it! When I am playing it on my phone even my dog sits and looks at the screen. I üíó playing this game in a frantic time like this. I can't have a minute were I'm not playing, thinking about it, or talking about it! This game makes me feel ü§™üòãüòç. I üíó it!", "It's a good time waster that's ruined by way to many ads that pop up freely on their own when you're just changing a tab in game. I wouldn't be so hard on it if it were just to watch the ads when you want to and get double payout or some type of reward.", 'Love it This game keeps me going and is very relaxing. But, when you get higher in the game, you have to watch an ad whenever you click on Mars. I like the app, but not the ads.', "I've always loved these games. They're my favorite evolution games. The only reason I'm not giving it 5 stars is because I ran into a bug that affected my gameplay. I contacted Tapps, but they have not responded. I hope no one runs into this bug too...", 'it literally shows you an ap every half minute. this is ridiculous', "Fabulous game, very addicting, adorable dogs and I'm definitely going to get into trouble for playing it too much when I'm not supposed to >:)", 'I redownloaded this game after over a decade just for the nostalgia. I will tell you now that this game did not disappoint. I still love this game, it is so cute and easy', 'I have played these games on and off for years and i love them! Funny, weird, cute and casual gaming, from getting far in the other evolution games i know it gets even weirder so i cant wait to see all the doggos. Very easy to learn.', 'Amazing! Its such an entertaining game and there are so many different types of dogs! There is a reasonable amount of ads and there is also lots of ways to make the process faster. I totally recommend it, it is a fun and simple game.', 'It\'s a good way to kill time, but I hate the new "evolution boxes" takes you out of gameplay and if I\'m just trying to tap, I cant do that anymore :(', "TO ALL THE PEOPLE WHO GAVE THIS A ONE STAR FOR THE ADS: There is a very free and simple trick to avoid these. TURN OFF YOUR WIFI. Ads can't get through without wifi to transfer it to your screen, so next time you think about complaining about the ads, remember: TURN OFF YOUR GOD DAMN WIFI", "Interesting time waster, but there are so many ads it ruins it. I can't even find the option to purchase the game just to turn off the excessive ads.", "This game is cool but... It has a LOT of ads. Its like they don't care adout there people who play their games. But it fun so if you don't care about ads play this game.", 'So fun! Lots of cute things to do and the doggos are great. All the little details in all of these games are great! (I have 5 from the same company thing)', "Ok think it's a good game but you need to make the poops cost more ,the diamonds easier to get and the cost of power ups cost less.", 'I have bad wifi so idk why ppl are complaining about the freaking adds i only saw 5-6 adds :/ but its simple, and cute, the designs, are, auhh, i like it but the designs, i dont like it.', "Literally everytime I try and open the app it crashesüíî I'm not sure if it's because of my device, but it's really sadüò≠ it's despair induuuuciiiingg- I've played it before though so it is a good game! I pray to Atua it will start workingüëâüëà", "The game is good but there are too many ads so I can't able to play the game properly so fix that issue.", 'Its a really fun and cool app to play. At the super market , the school bus , any where is fun to play', '100000/10 I had been grinding this game for a few years when I had my fire tablet and only had one dog and 2 alien dogs left until my brother smashed the tablet. Very enjoyable tho and I recommend to anyone <3', "You might find the ads annoying but don't worry! You can turn off your WiFi, you can play it offline and online!", "It's very fun and it helps waste time. The graphics are good and its super adorable üòä", "Game is nice, but too many cheap ads just keep popping up like every minute - they're ruining the experience.", "*its just an evolution game about dogs.* *that's it.* Yet it's so creative compared to other evolution games. So I give it a 10 out of 10.", 'Very fun, especially when waiting for someone or on a flight or when you need to pass time.', 'I love these games, they are just so much fun to play when ever I am waiting for anything from the end of my break to the bus.', "Ads always show up and it's annoying but I appreciate it when they give coins after watching ads :D", "Great app if you're bored, and inspirational characters. I even drew some of them. üíõ", 'I really liked this game, its really fun! Yes there are ads here and there either way its amazing! I really recommend this game! -this is my dad acc and im 12', 'THIS GAME HAS WAY TOO MANY POP UP ADS! Every minute or so.... The game will give you an ad, I say never get the game.', "pretty fun, kind of time consuming, gets boring after a while, but it's still fun", "It's a cute little time waster, but 3 ads in 1 minute is way too excessive.", "Very nice. Very nice. I loike it. Because it's very nice.", "It's SO FUN and the dogs are adorable‚ù§ this game is so addicting and I find myself playing it all day. I highly recommend it‚ù§", "I'm a dog person so I love this game and thanks for the update", 'This is is great, funny, and cute game I have no complaints please dont change anything about this game it is great', 'Great and awesome game üëç graphics are really clear great quality and controls Awesome make more of these please!']

title: with My DOG
description: ‚ñº‚ñºLife Changes, but Friendship Never Changes‚ñº‚ñº Attention: dog lovers and animal lovers, Spend more time with your puppies and get to know them. Various kinds and personalities. Let's start a new life with unique puppies. ‚ñºDogs in this game ‚ñº Shiba Inu, Toy Poodle, Chihuahua, Labrador Retriever and German Shepherd. More than 190 kinds of dogs with different fur colors and patterns. ‚ñºMeet new dogs at Friends Plaza ‚ñº Find the dog of destiny. Spend your time with the special one? or try to see how many dogs you can meet? Utilize Friends Hotel and Foster Parents as well. ‚ñºKeep a dog on your smartphone ‚ñº Interact with your puppy anytime, anywhere. Your puppy show you the tricks by recognizing your voice. The outside sceneries will change according to the time you actually spend. Take AR photos/videos of your dogs in your room or outside, and post them on SNS with #withmydog ‚ñºYour own family ‚ñº Costumes, hats, glasses and more. Unique items over 600 kinds. Give your puppy a stencil mark to make them special. Dog's room interior-decoration can also be customized. Free-to-play, a dog simulation game. Let's start a new life with a puppy. ‚ñº‚ñºAbout Neilo‚ñº‚ñº ‚ñºFollow us on: Twitter„ÄÄ@Neilo_JP Instagram„ÄÄ@withmy_friends_neilo ‚ñºOfficial HP: https://withmydog.neilo.co.jp/en/
summary: Pet your puppies, play together with toys, go for a walk together and more!

comments: ['Wanted to get "Little Friends" for the switch, found this which is actually done by the same people. Not disappointed at all, still has the origins of Nintendogs which I have missed. Need to add the ability to Bath your dog and give them treats though! Overall cute larl game, definitely wanting it on the switch too.', "As this is a newer kind of version of Nintendogs, I don't understand the point. You must pay for your own dog if it isn't a German Shepherd, and you can't change the fur color unless you pay to do so. May I add, you can't be under the age of twelve to make purchases. It wasn't my childhood, (I'm a Gen Z,) but I'm pretty sure the entire premise of Nintendogs was to choose your own pooch to make fun memories with.", 'This game is amazing!!!! 5 stars. Maybe in the future we can give our dogs a bath, treats and have a few more rooms, but otherwise this game is amazing!! Definitely the best dog care game. Cute graphics, clothes and furniture. I give this game 5 stars and hope everyone gives it a try. I absolutely love this game and recommend it to anyone looking for a nice dog game. Hopefully there will be lots of cool updates!!! Great work on this amazing game!!!', "Some Reasons I Gave This Game a 3 : 1. You cannot have play with a bunch of dogs in the same room only just one.. 2. Lots of the things in the shop are very expensive in my opinion... 3. It's also unfair for me because only the German Shepherd and the Toy Poodle are free but some of their colour tones you can have with Real Money... Soooooo those are my reasons, I know that they're a bit arrogant and shows the game's flaws but I think it's better to be honest even if the truth hurts!", "This game is forcing, I can hardly do what I want and at the start it says 'choose your first pet' or something along the lines, and you literally only have the option of a boring blonde thing. You get to choose the colours as black and white but you still end up with a boring blonde thing. Disappointing really.", 'I have the cat version too and absolutely adore both games. The creators anf developers really did a wonderful job. Iv looked for years and years for a Nintendogs type game and am so happy its finally here. Thankyou so much guys. Please can you add more dog breeds one day. This game is 10/10', "The graphics are good but everything else is a bust. Money money money. All this game cares about. You have to pay REAL MONEY just for your dog to learn ONE TRICK!! Like come on not cool. And in the begging it says to pick your dog, but it doesnt even let ME choose the dog. If I could give 0 stars, i would. But I can't. Heart broken this game is a pay to play thought I found a good game.", "This is an amazing game with lots of features!!!! I think towards the future this game could have maybe a few more dog breeds as well as more rooms, a bath feature, being able to give your dog a treat and maybe more personalitys for the puppys!!!!!! Other than that this it deserves 5 stars in my opinion and it's a great quality dog game simulation!! :D", 'I almost never leave low reviews. If I dislike a game I just move on. However, anyone thinking of playing this game should know that you will install the game, be forced to wait for another 400mb installation once you load the game, enter your birthdate, and then after all that the game randomly selects which pet you need to spend your time with. The others are locked behind a paywall. Isnt the point of the game to offer power of choice with a pet that fits your likes? I mean... just no.', "It's such a cute game, pretty similar to nintendogs. But that's why I love it! But i wish you you guys could add bubble baths for the dogs, bc it's more fun to wash them then brush. I also kinda want you guys to add treats, when a dog behaves u can give it a treat or when it does tricks :D", "Perfect for kids and nostalgic adults who grew up with Nintendogs. Has the most fair monetization I've seen in a free game (few ads. No cryptocurrency, prices are in dollars. Things like tricks that are paywalled are not necessary to enjoy gameplay, and prices are cheap) so parents can feel safe letting their kids play. Gameplay is Nintendogs lite. Not a lot of content, but very good at scratching that itch for a loving pet. First dog is random, but you can reset app until you get one you like", 'This is a good game, graphics are good, dogs are adorable, my one suggestion is that you add more dogs like Pomeranian, Great Dane, husky, but overall this game is fantastic üòä', 'Can you add more things to do? I cant get my lab friendship lvl past 11. I wish there was a online option also. I love this game but I just wish there was more to do and more breeds and colors.', 'Its okay, i love the graphic buy i wish everything didnt cost actual money, also i wish i could take them out on walks, interact with other dog/people etc.', "Great game high quality good graphics and good graphics and it's fun to play with the dogs but also make it so you don't have to use your voice for tricks also for all you saying they stole Little Friends: Dogs & Cats it is actually by the same people so they didnt steal it they just upgraded it and put it on mobile", 'I wanted to try it out because it looks like the same game as the popular Little Friends game for switch. Would have been nice if I could actually play though. Downloaded the content but the app would never start. Kept kicking me out. Really unfortunate.', "The shibas are so cute! But unfortunately every dog except for the toy poodle cost 5$ each (per color) it's clear that effort went into this game so I won't give 1 star but I believe that the page is misleading, advertising all the dogs you won't get. also this is a blatant Nintendogs ripoff", 'Save your time, game crashes on startup every single time. Not optimized well at all. I have a Google pixel 6 so nothing wrong on my end, again, save your time.', "It's a nice game although it says that there are 190 different breeds in the description. There only appears to be 8 and there's constant paywalls to unlock the dogs very misleading", "Also, first things first, I have this game on Switch too, BUT why the Switch version don't has the day night systhem like here?! I was so happy when I saw the same game here but with the Day night systhem! Csn't you update it to the switch version too? The graphics are OK I love it how it is. Sadly Is you have to pay for other dogs and colours but ok. At the end the games remember me here more to Nintendogs instead of the Switch cuz the day night systhem is missing..", "It's a really cute game.... But it keeps lagging, When I try to purchase something it crashes. Please fix the issue. Thanks", "Oh my god, finally a true successor to Nintendogs. I can't even tell you how badly I've been wanting something exactly like this on mobile. Just. Oh man this is fabulous. Thanks, devs!", "I like the it's simple and easy to interact with. I hope there's more breeds and more activities to play with. So far it's nice game and I'm looking forward for the updates of the game. üòäü§©", "Too bad they no longer update the game and haven't since 2022 üò© need more breeds and events, need more to do. It's a great game tho, reminds me of nintendogs haha üòÖ runs very well on phone üôèüèª", 'This app is very glitchy and has a lot of downloading at the beginning that takes forever to download.', 'Love the game but wished there was more stuff you could do with your fury friend. Like different compitions, with on walks meet other players.', "This i a good game can you just change it to where we can pick which dog we want because it picked out a dog for me that I didn't want and I can't change it.", "Trash tried atleast 19 times to boot it up but didn't let me play and just kicked me out I want to play my childhood game so fix it", "I like it, but why the only option is a bull dog and the colour is only black and white, it's a good game tho, but u need to fix the problem there.", 'Cool, i just play today, and i love it. It just like nintendogs üòç please add more free items üòÑ thanks üôèüèºüòÅ', "please update according to the sound of the dog and the breed, don't all sound the same....please also update so that the dog can grow bigger and add other features", 'This game is so fun and if you you have a dog that has to play this game can make you remind. I definitely 5 star.', "I love this game it is apsaloutlty amazing üíôüíôüíôüíôüíôüíôüí´üí´üí´üí´üí´üí´ wanted to put happy dog with hot dog gif but it wouldn't let me. I am now into marvel guardians of the galaxy so I wanted a dog named after my favorite character Nebula and I got a black and white shiba inu. I also wanted one named after Nebula's sister Gamora so I got a black and tan German shepherd. title: Puppr - Dog Training & Tricks
description:
Meet your new dog trainer! Puppr includes step-by-step video instructions to help you teach your dog basic obedience like ‚Äúsit‚Äù and ‚Äústay‚Äù to advanced tricks like ‚Äúfetch leash‚Äù and ‚Äúsit pretty‚Äù. Great for both new and experienced dog owners.

Features
‚Ä¢ Over 80 lessons taught by celebrity dog trainer Sara Carson & The Super Collies (America's Got Talent top 5 finalist)
‚Ä¢ Live chat with our team of world-class trainers to get your training questions answered (requires Puppr Premium subscription)
‚Ä¢ Step-by-step instructions with videos make lessons easy to follow
‚Ä¢ Built-in clicker makes training on-the-go easy. All lessons are taught with positive reinforcement!
‚Ä¢ Track your pup's training progress
‚Ä¢ Collect badges as you train and master new tricks
‚Ä¢ Support for multiple dogs
‚Ä¢ Puppr Shop that includes hand-picked product recommendations from Sara and the team to help with your training

Live Chat
Our team of professional trainers are available 24/7 to help with (but not limited to):
‚Ä¢ New puppy or dog
‚Ä¢ Unwanted behavior like puppy nipping, jumping on people, barking, etc
‚Ä¢ Leash training
‚Ä¢ Potty training
‚Ä¢ Separation anxiety
‚Ä¢ Trick training
‚Ä¢ Any training topic you need help with!

About Sara Carson & The Super Collies
Sara Carson is considered one of the top dog trick instructors in the world and was a top-5 finalist on season 12 of America's Got Talent. She and her dogs (Hero, Marvel, Hawkeye, and Fury) travel North America teaching dog trick workshops and performing with a popular stunt dog team. Sara and Hero currently hold the Guinness World Record for most tricks performed in 60 seconds (49 tricks!).

In-App Purchases
Puppr includes premium lesson packs that each come with 2 free lessons and additional locked content that can be purchased.

Subscription Pricing and Terms
Puppr offers two auto-renewing subscription options for Puppr Premium, which unlocks live chat and all the lesson packs. Pricing options are:
‚Ä¢ $12.99 per month
‚Ä¢ $99.99 per year (after a 7-day free trial)

These prices are for United States customers. Pricing in other countries may vary and actual charges may be converted to your local currency depending on the country of residence.

Your Puppr subscription will automatically renew at the end of each term and your credit card will be charged through your Google Play account unless auto-renew is turned off at least 24-hours before the end of the term. You can turn off auto-renew at any time from your Google Play account settings but refunds will not be provided for any unused portion of the term.

comments: ["Great app, without having to pay! Has most of the basics, and majority is free. The tips actually work, and now my dog has great grooming skills. Wish it had more interactions (people/cats/kids/dogs) or preventative/behavior training but it's a great groundwork without a personal trainer. I actually want to buy the extra thing but I don't have at the moment.", "Quality app, can't believe it's free. Breaks training down into very simple steps with helpful short video demonstrations. I subscribe to a paid app that is not as easy to use as this one. I'm not a fan of the in-app clicker but I guess it's a decent alternative if you can't afford an actual clicker. I would love to see expanded content for the future.", "I've had this app since it was released. The tricks keep growing and so do the features. It's a handy app. I've been training dogs since I was a kid. I don't specialize in trick training, so it's been quite helpful to have some more random fun tricks with a basic how to on training methods. Plus they keep adding tricks, so we'll have plenty of material for a while and I really like the new badge feature. All and all, its a fun, helpful app that both me and my dog enjoy!", "I'm a certified animal behaviorist, and I have enjoyed this app so much! The lessons are easy, the mechanics of the app work very well with the lessons. I love the simple, straightforward format for the menu, as well. Prices are incredibly low as well, and there's a surprising amount of free lessons available from the get go. Love this app, hope maybe you can add more about addressing specific behaviors perhaps?", 'This is an excellent app for training your dog new tricks. But, I gave 4 stars because there is a heavy emphasis on earning badges and there are no visual check marks on each completed item, which makes this feature lacking. I would like a better home screen with less clutter where I can upload a picture of my dog and have buttons to continue the lessons i left off.', 'I really enjoy this app! Only one I\'ve seen in a while where I want to buy the Pro and it\'s absolutely worth it. Well done on dog training explanations! Only reason it is 3 star instead of 5.. I can\'t open the "circus" trick jump through hoops arms without it erroring out "cannot play video"... I never asked it to play video! Then the app freezes and I have to close it entirely. If y\'all can get this working I\'ll change my stars n buy pro.', "Has helped me train my dachshund to do several tricks. (I can't think of higher praise. ) I haven't bought additional packs yet, but it seems fair & I'm glad it's not all or nothing. The way tricks are broken down helped me recognize when to be patient, when to try something different. (Plus: what to try!) I wish I could use the clicker without opening the app but there doesn't seem to be an API call for that accessible from automation.", "The steps are really easy to follow. I had reservations on if it would work, I was pleasantly surprised,that they actually worked, we've now completed the basics and are on the silly training. If you want an app to help you training your new puppy, then this is the perfect one to use.", 'Wow! This was exactly what I was looking for: concise written instructions with short demonstration videos, no ads, and an elegant and intuitive interface. If I could give this 6 stars I would. After trying about 10 different dog training apps, I found this one, and it is the best by far. I rarely leave reviews but this app is just exceptional. The free content is so good I will happily and gladly support the app developers by purchasing the additonal content. Good stuff.', 'This is a great app for dog training. It was very helpful and u got to teach my dog great tricks like spin and how to hug someone. So cute. The only thing is alot of tricks are locked that you have to pay for. Same with the chat with experts. You can ask professionals for help or this and tricks but that also costs money. If you are willing to pay for those things, this app is easily five stars.', 'I absolutely love this app! I love having a visual as well as words when teaching my dog, so seeing that helps. my dog responds well to all the techniques used, I definitely recommend this app! Cant wait till my dog can roll herself in a blanket haha...easy to use and clear instructions, just amazing and free!', "This app is overall not that bad. I think it'd be very helpful to a beginner dog owner, BUT..Over half the tricks are locked and need to be paid for, which I really dislike. Don't get me wrong, I've taught my dog a new trick from this app,and it's pretty easy to use,but I just wish there were a few more options without having to pay for it.", "This app is amazing especially if you don't want to spend money! you can still teach your dog simple commands for FREE! THIS really helped and actually worked out great! But if you would like to teach your dog more harder selections you would have to pay money but not a lot like you would expect.", "This training is super easy to follow! Our shows both infatuation step by step and a video for each step which replays over and over. It sets up both you and your dog for successful training! My 9 week old dog knows her name, Come, Stay, Sit, and is create trained and clicker trained! We are working on others and can't wait for advanced training. The only issue I have is when the buttons stop working. The fix is to close the app and restart, so it's not a big deal.", "Great start. Simple, basic and easy to follow. Best part, it's effective training for your dog. I have a 3 month old beagle and we doing great using this app. She is progressing on sit and down after only a few sessions. On to come and stay over the next few days. Even thinking about purchasing some of the advance training but that's a ways off still. Highly recommend. Gives you needed structure to follow. Very helpful in my opinion.", 'This app is amazing! So easy to use and informative! I\'ve been searching for proper guidance, as a first time "dog mom" it can be very complicated to do online research on your own. I was feeling overwhelmed, there is so much information out there and it\'s so generalized...I was struggling trying to find the right advice for us. This app has helped more than any other source I\'ve come across! I\'m so grateful and I most definitely recommend it!', 'I really like the app, I didn\'t realize you had to pay to access ALL of the training though. Wish it was free, but I understand that people need to make money. Left off a star because it isn\'t \'free" like advertised. Each training is a video and step by step description.', "This app didn't help much. it seems like the instructions would help, but when I tried to teach them down, I said, Sit and all they did when I put the treat down thr got up and just bent down to grab it I tried other things to and it didn't work. This app wasn't really the best app for me.", 'Not useful. The tracking of the tricks is very poor, with only few options (not trained, in progress and trained) which isnt useful. I need more detail or customization, where you can rate the dogs performance and specify in what part of the training your are working (inside home, in the garden, in the street, with people etc). The app also keeps disconecting my dog profile and showing an empty one.', "I just started using this app and I absolutely love it. The tutorials themselves are clear and concise and each skill has a short video clip that shows someone teaching their dog that skill, so it's perfect whether you're a visual learner or prefer step-by-step instructions.", "I bought the full app. I really enjoyed the free demonstrations and paid for one of the packages then paid for the full app to get everything. The tricks definitely depend on the dog. Some I had to modify the steps to teach my dog, some tricks are very difficult and not explained great from the videos provided. I was between 3 and 4 stars but have enjoyed it more than a mear 3 stars. If your enjoying the free performances then try out some of the paid content. I'm reviewing this app after 1 year", "I LOVE this app, I've bought the full lesson packs, so I have them all, however I've only given it 4 stars, because the updates/new lesson packs always come out on the iPhone first. I understand that is because most people use iPhones, but normally after a few months the new lesson packs become available on Android. Well, I've been waiting months and months for Charming 2.0, and other packs, to no avail. Hopefully they'll become available to Samsung soon, because I do love this app so much. ‚ù§", '1000% recommend! This app is so thoughtfully designed to help you teach your dog a large variety of new skills of all difficulty levels. It is so easy and fun to use, and breaks down each skill/trick in simple steps, visuals, along with helpful tips!', "On many levels I've been very impressed with this app. The instructions are simple and easy to implement and I love the clicker option. What is keeping me from giving this five stars is that I'm not seeing a heeling/loose leash category. This is one of my biggest struggles with my 18-month-old 81 lb Doberman. I don't mind paying for it but I am very disappointed if it's not included somewhere. Please let me know if I've missed it!", "This is an easy to use app and breaks the tricks down easily. The basics and clicker are free but you have to pay for the fancy stuff, but it's reasonably priced and worth it if you want to learn some cool party tricks to show off and blow your friends' minds!", "I love this app. I have been training dogs for years but never trick training, the app is very easy to follow and pictures make it beginner friendly. A lot of people complain about paying but don't understand that classes to learn all of the tricks would cost hundreds of dollars so only paying $12 is an absolute steal.", "This would have been such an amazing app if you were able to lock anywhere on it to get the clicking sound. If only the clicker button was in the middle of the app. It's quite difficult to use practically when training, because one has to search for the clicker button and that's not very user-friendly. Such a pity.", "I love this app it is so so so helpful and very easy to use! I love the built-in clicker it makes training so much easier! 10 out of 10 would recommend! I had a question though this app was recommended to me for the chat feature and I'm not seeing it anywhere I have purchased all of the training packs and I thought it might come with that but I still don't see it? Even without this feature it has helped me so much just curious!", 'Great training room with videos for many of the tricks to help guide you through the steps. Hopefully they will continue to add more tricks, video tutorials, and badges. Built in clicker for those who need it. Make tricks easy to understand and teach. Would love to see the next update add "carry an object" or to "pull a toy while walking". Also would love to see a section for the different AKC Trick Dog Tittles and CGC standards.', 'Good instructions, but you have to pay in order to access all the tricks and the "badges" don\'t work, I\'ve completed many of the tasks, and the ratio on each badge shows I\'ve completed it, but the app doesnt recognize it for some reason. Kind of disappointed, could be great', "Much easier to use than a dog training book with step by step guide and videos. I can keep a record of my dog's progress and the inbuilt clicker is handy. There's the option to purchase individual packs of additional tricks, or all additional tricks.", 'Epicccc It really help and there are some cool tricks on here. Some even help with obedience training thank you!! But one request is that maybe give more access( not having to pay) for the cooler tricks like jumping over your arm, or sitting/standing on your feet while in the air ( i dont remember the name) but i know u need that to keep the app running. Anyways thanks for showing me some tricks, and stuff, its really useful for my energy ball.', "super helpful for training! love the variety of tricks and the little clicker sound! my most favorite part of this app is even if you don't pay to subscribe you have access to all the basics of training and step by step techniques. very well executed.", 'I love this app and downloaded it shortly after its release (and went premium). The photos are beautiful and the steps are easy to follow. The ONLY reason I give it four stars is my primary device is ios has way more trick packs and even a store. No word on social media if they are working an update for android in the near future.', 'I paid for the upgrade hoping to get the additional lessons, which I was really hoping to use. Except these are only available on iOS and not Android (which is not clearly stated...if at all). I essentially paid to have someone via "chat" tell me I don\'t get the additional lessons on an Android device. What a waste of money. So if you have Android, be warned and don\'t pay for the upgrade.', "Hello. I've had Puppr for a while now, and my dog has learned some pretty cool tricks, like Shake. (I call it Paw) but here's the parts that make me feel a bit upset: 1. Some of the lesson packs, well... You have to pay for them. 2. It needs more lessons that are actually FREE! I mean, the basic pack IS fine, but I feel like, my dog needs more things to learn... 3. I don't think the notification for training actually makes a sound. But other than that it's fine But I also have ideas pls send web", "The overall idea here is good. Although, they really need to do one of two things. 1. Make the clicker button centered and bigger or 2. Have a clicker only mode where clicking anywhere on the app will trigger the sound. When you have an energetic puppy, it's difficult the track down the clicker.", "I have not used this app yet, but impressed it teaches how to load the clicker or give it meaning to the dog. A lot of clicker training leaves this important step out. Looking forward to using the app as another way of bonding with my dog. I don't care for things like the rock back sit, but I can change up those things. After looking thru the app. there isn't enough my dog can learn from it so twelve bucks is just not worth it, for others it could be a lot of fun.", 'Homestly way better than the other apps. The free content is vast whereas other apps have you pay a lot just to use content that is otherwise free. The instructions and the videos are super simple and short. Honestly great great grear job to the developers.', "This ap is so amazing. I have a great pyrenees who is extremely hard to train. He's very low energy, and very independent so it's extremely hard to motivate him. He recently got sick, and threw all his potty training out the window. We got him as an adult, and this ap walked us through the RIGHT way to potty train a dog. Now he's back to his old self after some blunders. He's making amazing improvements. Thank you Puppr!!!"]

title: Dog Scanner: Breed Recognition
description: The Dog Scanner app will identify your dog's breed reliably in just a few seconds! Besides taking a picture, you can also record a video or upload an image from your gallery. Got a mixed breed? No problem, the Dog Scanner app also recognizes mixed breeds! We provide you with detailed data and interesting facts about the different breeds of your mixed breed dog. No dog around? Doesn‚Äôt matter! The Dog Scanner app also recognizes humans: Simply scan yourself, your friends, your family or the people around you and find out which dogs you resemble the most! ------ NEW! Become a part of our Dog Scanner community! Share your results and compare them to the results of the community! Upload pictures of your favorite dog to our Social Feed and share them with other dog lovers! Have a look at the profiles and photos of other users, like and comment on posts from our dog community and filter them by date or popularity! Additionally, you can easily share your posts with your friends by simply sending a picture directly from the Dog Scanner app. ------ NEW! Catch all dog breeds and become an expert! Catch all the dog breeds with our Gamification feature ‚Äì just like in Pok√©mon Go! Master the challenges, earn virtual treats and become a true dog expert! Compete with your friends or users from the community and climb to the top of our ranking list! ------ All dog breeds in the Dog Scanner app! The Dog Scanner app currently identifies more than 370 different dog breeds, including all breeds officially recognized by the F√©d√©ration Cynologique Internationale (FCI) and even some more! Our comprehensive database with information and pictures of all dog breeds (including the unofficial ones) can also be accessed completely without scanning! Give us feedback on the Dog Scanner app! Let us know if the dog‚Äôs breed has been correctly identified. If not, you will get useful tips to improve your own results. If you also indicate which dog breed is in the picture, you help us to enhance our software since the app automatically learns how to provide even more accurate outcomes. Also suggest or vote for (unofficial) dog breeds that you want us to add to the app in the future! Get your premium upgrade! With our premium version, the app will no longer show ads and your results will be available faster. Furthermore, you can now choose whether your dog breeds should be recognized rather quickly or with higher accuracy. With the premium version, scanning dogs is also possible in offline mode, so you no longer need an active internet connection to identify their breeds. With the optional in-app purchase of our premium version, you will also help to support this app. ------ Find us on social media! On our social media channels we provide you with the most beautiful dog pictures from the community. You will also find many interesting facts about man's best friend. Furthermore, we will keep you updated on all new added features of the Dog Scanner app in the future. * Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/dogscanner_app * Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/DogScannerApp * Twitter: https://twitter.com/dogscanner_app ------ Just give it a shot! Dog recognition as easy as it gets! Despite the small app size you will get all features and be able to identify a dog‚Äôs breed or get access to our extensive database at any time! Before you consider getting an expensive DNA test, simply scan your dog with the app and the dog breed will automatically be determined within seconds! Download the Dog Scanner app now!
summary: See a dog, but don't know its breed? Just take a picture and find out!
