comments: ["Don't buy..This app is useless if u need it over the amount of time pass the phone activity..Once the phone close out and you now have to put your code back in to wake the phone back up that is the only way the phone will stay active..if you are not home to do that the video will not play ..Rippp off!!", 'We are loving this app. It certainly puts our minds at ease knowing our girls are behaving, especially when we live in a strata. I must remember to leave a light on at night & change the sensitivity on the noise as it seems to pick up all noises apart from barking, although we can go through the activity log for a more precise recording if need be. Well done on a great app.', "This is a fantastic dog monitoring app and it's great especially if you have a spare phone at home with good camera. You can watch your dog anytime and speak to it too. There is unfortunately some video lag when you are using different network to connect. If the video compression is better, it would help alot. Another feature would be if the dog can see me in the dog station screen as well. Overall still great!", "Excellent app with ni extra costs on it. Easy to use with good tutorials in-app to get the most out of it. In my dog's case did help to stop the loud crying thst was disturbing the neighbors. But, i did notice suddent disconnections during my whole work shift being away having battery optimization disabled for the app. I hope this issues can be fixed. Or at least notify when the the app loses it. (A full bug report has been sent explaining all with details to support team) Great job, recommend!", "The devs seems to have thought of everything great app. Automatic recording, constant audio while also being able to watch the video would be awesome extras Id want, especially as I can't always monitor my dog.  I was able to resolve issues with the app going to sleep by putting my phone in performance mode, and they provide some documentation to support these issues for samsung users.", "This is a great app. After some research i found this to be the best app out there. I had an old ipad that i didn't use for years. Now i can use it as a station to monitor my cat ( not sure why it meant to be for dogs only). And the beauty is that I monitor my pet from an android phone. so no issue with communicating with different platforms. I give it 4 starts becuase i wish it has the follwoing: 1- I can monitor by video and listen same time. 2- app to save video / shot when pet is noisy", "The app was working great the first week but then the dog monitor kept disconnecting. I followed all the suggestions to make sure nothing is interrupting the app and I even reinstalled it, but it keeps happening. The worst part is I can't reconnect to the dog monitor until I personally go to my tablet to connect it again.", "I wish this app had two things: (1) a method to custom set what level of noise you want notifications for and (2) a way to save the record of sound. It was a great fit when I monitored my foster in his crate, but to monitor him left out the crate the app either lists the background noise as him being noisy or, if I tell it to put the volume down a notch, it doesn't mark medium level noises.", "The video streaming is very very bad. At all times I just getting the pop up, video streaming unavailable, and the screen video just freezes. Question on the 4G, my WhatsApp call was seamlessly working, so would request you to kindly look into your networking stream and help sort this issue at the earliest, otherwise I'll like to request a refund.", "Dog monitor does a good job of handling dog monitoring. The default camera zoom on the phone side is a bit too tight. I'd rather zoom in than start with a format that fills the width or height of the screen I'm on. Since I have an extra tall screen, the aspect ratio is quite off compared to the video at home. This is adjustable in the settings, as noted by TappyTaps in the the reply to this review.  There's still lots of possibilities for added functionality: - Video analysis to indicate activity - Dog station side activity logging, that can be seen on the person station even if monitoring is stopped for a period - Automatic storage of video in noisy/active periods on the dog station, with settings for quality and max storage used  Still it's a very good app that does what it says.", 'This app worked once when i first installed it. After that first time the video stopped working, but the audio still was fine. After several weeks of the audio working, the app just stopped working all together. It would just disconnect the other phone automatically. Waste of money.', "Running the dog station on an old Huawei Honor 6X, camera isn't the best (not the apps fault) but it gets the job done. Only wish the low light performance was a bit better and that short video clips could save along with the sound. Otherwise very good stop gap between nothing at all and buying a dedicated pet camera. Unfortunately it seems work on this app has ceased and moved on to the subscription based Barkio. At the time of my review, the last update was in November 2020.", "Can't install or get a refund! Used this app previously on an iPhone and ipad and worked fine. A few years later I am now on Samsung devices. Can install on one phone but won't download or install on the second device as it says i already own the app; yes I don, on the first device but I need it on the second too!! Tried requesting a refund and can't!! Very disappointed as was a good app a few years back when I used it", 'It does what it says. But the picture comes across pixelated and the video is 100% glitchy. Wish it was better quality. Love the adjustable settings for the dogs being loud. Also wish you could have 2 phone hooked up to one tablet.', 'great app, good quality although there is a delay with everything. still very happy and impressed. even after the "developers" response, I think the app could use some touch up. Still a great app. lower the price to 2.99 and then when you fix the bugs charge what you are charging. 5.99 for Android users', "I have never had lag issues due to the app- it was always my connectivitybeing a jerk. This is easy to use. It requires two devices, but let's face it, most of us have an old phone lying around that we can set up somewhere for this and just plug into a wall. Overall, I love it and it gives me peace of mind when I'm out of the house!", 'The app works but I was surprised to find out that there is no way for user login when you use different platforms, and as a result I had to pay twice - one for my iPad and one for my android phone. This in my option should have been one payment that gives an account access to two devices regardless of platform... Or I wish I was informed when I downloaded it that the price would be doubled if u hv two platforms', "It's everything I needed but has a major inconvenience as it cannot work in background which means I cannot play my pet's favourite YouTube video meanwhile. The pet station drains way too much power so my old nexus shuts down even if charging. I wanted to use it for my parrot so it could be a good idea to customise the icon.", "Pretty good app, only issue is I can't seem to watch the live video feed as it keeps coming up with error messages. I like how it records the noises made so you can go back and review them, which is handy if you have a barking dog.", "My girlfriend and I just got this for our little one because we suspect he has sepration anxiety and it's been amazing. We love that we can check on him when we get notifed of a noise, talk to him or record our own phrases. The only reason it doesn't get 5 stars is of minor. it would be awesome to record footage or a clip, Not a lot, like 5-10 seconds.Like Twitch clips. Second: It has problems streaming through a wifi vpn.Only pics. Third: It would be great to have a chrome extension to view.", 'A great app for monitoring your dog (or whatever else you need to monitor). Some small issues with the speaker picking up your voice and making your voice to echo and the person station have freezed a few times. Otherwise all good!', 'i would have got a refund but ran out of time on google play to request it and did not think i could. the app works but your phone screen timeout will not work. i will never use this app if it is going to force my phone to be on all day. doesnt matter how dim the screen is, it will screen burn when you have it on all day every day. if you make it so the screen time out still works i will gladly use this and give 5 stars.', "App has stopped working. says it can't connect to the dog monitor server, have tried reinstalling on both devices and connecting through alternative networks. have had to pay for this item twice so I'd appreciate if this problem was resolved", "Hands down the best dog Monitor app out there. Multi platform so I can use my old iPhone to watch the dogs and having a live feed at all times is absolutely terrific. When I don't want to hear the constant scratching of their claws moving around on the floor I can mute the sound and it'll still give me a notification if they're barking (at lower mic sensitivity) I have two recommendations: 1 build a Windows App for desktop usage 2 offer a way to lower video framerate for streaming performance", 'Video quality is poor when transmitted, by having the app auto turn on do-not-disturb it prevents commands feom playing, and when I tried to get a refund within the 30 minutes of purchasing, google says that the app refund is not supported by its policy. I like the idea of this but will not recommend it', 'Amazing! Simple to use, reliable and one time purschase. Just brought my dog to a new city and the fact im able to see, listen and talk with him makes this transition so much easier. Thanks devs for making the app and not adding subscription plans on it! Keep at it!', "I am unable to play the commands and speak to the dog via the bluetooth speakers connected to my iPad. The commands and voice feature only functions when it's coming directly out of the ipad but not when connected to speakers! this is causing issues any dog can hardly hear me.", "In the end, I couldn't use it, because in my particular setting the quality of audio and video was too bad for practical use. The company was very kind and cooperative to do a refund, thank you!", "This app is asking me to pay twice when using the same google account. Have followed all instructions correctly. When I try to pay the second time returns an error saying I already own the app and refuses to let me download it! So it's unusable at this point. Edit: this issue was resolved with assistance of the development team (see advice below) and the app is now working fine.", 'The app has been super helpful in identifying when our dog is noisy while we are out, so that we can help give her the best home life possible. Not quite 5 star as you cannot currently export the logs, only the recordings of noises. Would still recommend.', "Still trying to use it. I paid for the app on my phone and it says to pair with another device. It has no option to just download, only to pay on Google app store, but I can't pay to download because it says I already own the product on my Google account. Would love some help.", 'the picture and sound quality is horrible. it picks up the slightest sounds. and I had to purchase 2 times, once on my phone and another on my tablet . definitely not worth it.', 'I just got it and I generally believe this is really really good, the fact that you can record your own voice and save them onto the tablet so that your dog can hear your voice from home is really convenient. My tablet dies fairly quickly so I just plugged it in so that it has power at all times', 'The app works pretty well. My concern is my screen. Even at the lowest brightness it is going to ruin my screen by burning an image in permanently. I highly suggest updating the app to have a complete black screen. Also the app is called Dog Monitor and we are using it for our Cats :/', "Only thing is it would be better is using android and mac os you didnt have to pay google play and app store.... 2 times but worth the 799 x 2 because it works flawlessly and is worth way more than the 14 bucks I paid. Notifies you logs all your noises so you dont need to actively watch and let's you know when there noise. Dont waste your money on a furbo get this instead.", 'An amazing app, to check on my little guy, and keep him "company" by talking and comfort him if he complains. It works perfectly even in longer distances. I love it. Thank you!!!! üëçüëç', "The description says we can check on the dog using two phones or tablets. But we have to purchase the app for all the three devices (1 dog station and 3 person stations). I couldn't even test the app even after purchasing because of this.", 'I just love this app!! had a problem a few months back and sent them a message and they fixed it :) thank you so much for this app it really helps me daily and i just love the fact that they can hear you too when you need them too. Thank you for the best app ever.', "This has worked well to get an idea how our dog spends her day while we're away. it's great to be able to run through, review and share the audio. It would be nice if the video also recorded the snippets when the sound did.", "This app is just amazing! We were afraid to leave our puppy home alone without knowing how he was going to react, but this camera has made it easy for us to watch him and talk to him when he starts barking or chewing on stuff he shouldn't be chewing on! I work an hour away but I'm still able to have him near me with this app!"]

title: Dog Game - The Dogs Collector!
description:
With cute art and adorable mini-games, you‚Äôll be caring for your puppies in Dog Game any chance you get! Thousands have given Dog Game two furry paws up! üêæ

Dog Game is simple yet highly-addictive! To play, all you need to do is collect different kinds of cute & unique dogs and build a home for them, your very own Dog Tower! You can craft decoration and create lovely rooms to unlock cute new puppies to fill them with every single day.

Collect adorable dogs like shiba inu, husky, pug, bulldog, golden retriever and beagle! There‚Äôs over 900 puppys you can collect! üí´ Decorate rooms in your dog towers with your favourite styles: unicorn, fancy, legendary, anime, magic and so many more!

‚óè 900+ kawaii puppies to collect!

‚óè Play special events and earn exclusive pups & prizes
‚óè Enter contests to design the most adorable rooms
‚óè Play fun & addictive mini-games to earn coins
‚óè Join a club & play with your friends (and make new ones)
‚óè Compete in the leaderboard for exclusive rewards
‚óè Daily missions & contests!
‚óè There‚Äôs something new every week!


üè† DECORATE YOUR OWN PUPPY TOWER

Create & personalize an adorable dog tower for all of your puppies to live in! Craft adorable decorations like plants, couches, dog toys, windows, sandcastles and adorable animal furniture.

You will adopt dogs of different themes and vibes according to your own taste! 70‚Äôs, beach, dance club, farm, underwater, or royalty. 


üíñ PLAY GAMES WITH FRIENDS

Dog Game is a great pet game to play with friends! You can enter contests where you compete by designing the best dog room! You will play with dog lovers across the world! Dog Game is an amazing way to make new friends and socialize in new clubs!

Enter fun events throughout the year where you can earn unique rare dogs and special prizes! Unlock new challenging levels by playing minigames! 

Participate in non-stop dog-themed games like:
‚óè BarckyBlocks: Match blocks like in tetris and beat all high scores
‚óè PuppyPops: Match adorable dogs and earn lots of coins
‚óè Spin the Basket
‚óè And more!


‚ú® YOUR VIRTUAL PET AWAITS YOU IN DOG GAME

Your future pups are waiting for you now! Put your paws to work, play with friends & clubs, and get Dog Game today for free!

comments: ['Been playing this game for over a year and have really enjoyed it. Recently though, the events are just reskins of either floors from Cat Game or repeats of already past events. While a little repeat is to be expected, it just seems like they stopped caring about working on this game. Getting to the point where I am done with the regular tower and there are no options to continue, unless I spend actual money. Getting a little disappointed, because it is a fun game most times.', "This app won't work properly for me. I downloaded it, chose my starter dog, then it went to the house and the only thing it showed was the floor and the dog I chose. No tutorial. I thought it was just like that and I've played the cat game, so I fed her and even got two decos as well as the next dog. But I ran out of food and nothing. I couldn't do anything. So I closed the app and got back in and it restarted. From the beginning where you choose the dog.", "I've played dg for 2 yrs and cg for 1 yr. Lately cg has become unplayable due to lag. I worry the same will happen here after having invested thousands of hrs and $. Dog Game lacks some features from Cat Game & the crafting + leveling is overall more difficult. It lacks a full VIP reward system as well. My biggest issue is with player support. Often we feel ignored with our feedback & concerns. We know we won't get help from certain support staff. Bugs are left unfixed & there is no compensation", 'Really great game with awesome drawings. The one thing that I would complain about is the ads; right after you play a mini game,it just gives you a pop-up ad. I believe this is similar to the cat game, so if you are interested in the game, this game will surely spark your interest.', "Great game! I really love it and I enjoy it. I think it runs smoothy and it's really fun to collect dogs. I do have one thing that bothers me. Recently I've been having to uninstall and reinstall the game because it keeps glitching. Whenever I load the game up and I'm waiting in the loading screen once it gets to 100% the dog glitches out and then my screen goes black. Nothing happens after that and it's been happening recently. I hope this can get fixed. It's still a great game, love it!", "Cute and fun time waster about collecting dogs! I haven't been able to put it down! For such a simple concept it sure is fun. It's a bit money hungry but not overly so. A purchase removes ads, at least. They are generous with premium currency so that's always a plus. It would be nicer if there were more than 2 mini games to earn coins, though. Overall I'm happy with this game. The dogs are super cute, there are a ton of different ones (real and fantasy) and the wait times are not that bad!", "The cuteness can't be denied, and I love how every dog has their own unique animation - that makes the collecting all the more worthwhile! My main gripe is that advancing depends heavily on crafting, which takes a good amount of both resources and coins, which are hard to earn with only two mini games. There's a whole lot of waiting involved (wait for boxes to be delivered, wait for food options to be refreshed, wait for crafting to be completed) and the minigames are both pretty short plays.", "I really love the game but I've recently started having issues with booting the game up. It will load the start screen and once it starts loading, it give me a black screen and I can no longer play it. I've uninstalled and reinstalled it a couple of times and it loads my save, vut after a few times of playing, it give me the dreaded black screen again. Not sure who to contact because the black screen won't really allow me to contact anyone. üòï", "Recently it's just been glitching out at the loading screen and going black. I've been trying for a week or so now just to get loaded into the game, but it will instead freeze up and sometimes make me restart my phone entirely. It was fun for a bit, I guess, and I like it more than CG because I'm a dog person... but it is quite literally unplayable.", "This is my updated review! It took a few trys to actually get the game to the point where i had a game id and it would save my progress. The game is addicting but you have to be lucky with the spins in the beginning to actually be able to move on. Its not a problem after you get past the tutorial part but in the beginning if you keep getting dogs then you don't have enough supplies to continue and you have to start over. This needs to be fixed for future players! It is still a pretty fun game!", "its awsome! i love it so cute the one thing that bothers me is when you get a puppy it comes in a basket and when you get to a higher level it take soo long to get out of the basket but it isn't to big of a problem so i still give it five stars its a very fun game so i recomend it its very cute i play it so much", "I really love the game:) 1. No issues 2 . No laggy stuff 3. Not a lot of ads 4.Really fun and colorful 5.a lot of reskins from cat game but I don't mind", "After continuously getting the black screen when trying to load, I deleted the game then re-installed it. It worked! But now it's doing the same thing AGAIN. I'm missing another event because of these issues, and I did very much enjoy the game. This whole situation, however, is really souring my opinion and enjoyment, ESPECIALLY due to the developers' lack of action and response.", "I LUV it!!! It's SOOO cute and fun. I very rarely rate 5 starts so be proud of yourself! Very underrated! I don't even get pop up adds! 100% recomend! Update: I'm changing my rating. Its not letting me play anymore. Only thing I can do is click the play button. I can hear the music but after I click the play button it brings me to a black screen and nothing happens. Just the music playes. Pls fix.", "It's cute but it gets old doing the same two mini games over and over to earn coins. And sometimes when you watch an ad, it completely freezes the game (sometimes my phone too) and then crashes. Also the percentage of landing a dog the further you go is annoying. I want to continue to get more rooms, not collect an over amount of materials.", "the game doesn't work. it makes me restart the game every time and it doesn't show anything but the dogs. no tutorial or menu. nothing.", 'I love this game, from the art to the gameplay its highly addictive. I do suggest it to everyone, as a dog lover i love every piece of it! To the devs thank you so much for making it. Have a nice day', "This game is super fun to play casually when you need something to do. The mini games are super user friendly and super helpful when you need some coins. The crafting section is great, but my only complaint is that it takes a while to get a dog in any room, and my barbecue room has a huge amount of cotton before there's even a chance you can get a dog. Other than that, not disappointed!‚ò∫Ô∏è", "The game is cute. Its just as fun as cat collector, which I've played for almost 3 years now. But this one has too any ads! After each round of game play there is an ad before you get your coins. Ger rid of that please! There is a glitch in the doggopedia, I can't see most of my dogs, and when I scroll through it, it doesn't work correctly. Each time I deliver a basket or feed for supplies, instead of going back where I was, I'm taken to the top of the tower. It's just frustrating.", "Crafting recipes are so difficult. Would definitely like to see them be changed to be like Cat Game's recipes. An option to permanently opt out of global chat (CG got this recently) would be amazing. I think the % chance of getting a dog is a lie, feels like I have to wait and spin so many times before I get one. I love this game, I'm enjoying it even more than CG (that I've played for 2+ years and am almost max level on). With a few tweaks, I think it'll be perfect!", "This game has been a lot of fun so far. The dogs are super cute and my 4yr old daughter absolutely loves them all. Problem now is that the game was asking me to update, but it hasn't üòï had the spinning circle the entire day. Tried resetting my phone, nothing. Tried turning it off then back on, nothing. I even tried Uninstalling to see if that would work but now it won't even let me re-install! ü•∫ Please help fix this bug!", "This game is sooo cute!! I definitely recommend it. It does have very few ads, but it can take a really long time to get a basket. Otherwise, It's very fun!", "Amazing game! I love the designs and animations, foods are cute. I love every dog and I'm attached to all of them! I just hate the fact that you have to wait for a very very long time because then I either have to do random stuff for the long time on the game or just leave and go back later which annoys me a bit. Good game overall though", 'i loved cat game so much even though i\'m a dog person so obviously i\'m super into dog game! it really is the best. (1.) it\'s calming without being boring. (2.) you never run out of things to do, but there\'s no stressful feeling of like "ugh it\'s too much work." (3.) there\'s mini games! and the adorable dog home decor challenges? ugh yes, so fun! (4.) the mini games are actually fun and you get coins for playing them. i\'d love a unicorn version in the future!', "Very cute game. I love this game and CG, but I play this more since I'm more of a dog person than a cat person. The only real issue I have with it is that sometimes the loading gets stuck at around 55%, and I have to restart the app to get back to the home screen. The premium keys aren't very easy to get as the only way is through completing floors, and it would be great if you could add the ability to add friends and private messages!", "Recently been having issues with the game loading, I get a blank screen with music playing. I've tried on two separate phones and tried re-downloading it. When it does finally load it works for a few minutes and then crashes. Seems to be an issue for a lot of people right now, so hoping it can be fixed soon.", "I really liked it to start. Got all the way to level 23 and suddenly got stuck on a black screen. I uninstalled and reinstalled and had to start all over. Support says they can't help me because the game added random numbers to the end of my screenname and I don't know them. Started all over and now it's stuck on the black screen again when I try to open it. I think I'm done.", "I enjoy this game a lot, super cute and fun to play, I love the different themes :) Edit: As I level up, the chances are becoming too low, and collecting is difficult. I'm only level 15 - hope to see some tweaks in this area as the game has so much potential!", "It's basically the cat game, but with dogs! I've loved the cat game since my friend introduced me to it a few years ago, and when my sibling brought this to my attention I couldn't pass up the opportunity to play. Aside from minor stylistic changes it's the same; so it's perfect to play when I'm waiting on things to craft in the cat game (and vice versa) While it seems a little odd to have the same themes as paid for floors in the cat game be free in this one, that's really the only flaw imo", "Very annoying. After waiting for a few months for it to catch onto some of CG's better qualities and not just compile its worst the game only presented a black screen every time I attempted to log into it. For two days, everytime I tried to get into the heart of the app this happened. Since I know the first thing is always suggested to Uninstaller and reinstall, I did that and the game started me over and says backup and restoring can't be done. What a waste.", 'Definitely a super fun game. Crafting is a little harder than Cat Game but still really fun. Great support too. They just restored both of my accounts after having to get a new phone and not being able to get back into my old Google Play account. The only thing I wish they would allow is for us to be able to gift more than 10 items at a time to club members requesting items.', "Was looking for a cute collection game with a very specific want for a clean colorful style, and this + cat game fits the bill very well. I like to support games I'm fond of so I've allowed myself to purchase ONE floor from each, and otherwise haven't felt compelled to purchase anything at all to proceed. I do wish there were more mini games I admit, a simple endless runner I believe would go over really well, but all in all a lot of fun, can't complain!", "I wrote this review on the cat alternative so I figured I'd mention it here too. It's an amazing game but there are some wifi troubles. It could just be me but for both games I have to frequently switch my wifi on and off because you need wifi to play but the game won't load when it's on. Sometimes you need wifi to do things and sometimes you can play offline perfectly fine which is weird. Other than that it's sooo adorable and I highly recommend it!!", "Also having the black screen after the loading as others are reporting. A little disappointed that it's right in the middle of an event and more disappointed now that I may get auto-booted from my club before this gets fixed. I'm really trying to hang in there because I enjoy Cat Game so much, but it's getting very difficult.", "An inferior version of Cat Game, which is a shame cause I really love the cute dogs as well. Crafting is such a nightmare though - both regular and events. It's not nearly as much of a slog to get through levels twice as high up as the ones in my little dog tower. Feels like they want you to spend money to move faster but nah. I'd get more for my money from their own other product.", "Changed my rating. We had to get to like the 4th floor before we were able to quit the game and have it save. My son and I both downloaded this. Played it a bunch. I got to the second level with 2 dogs when I stopped playing. Next time I went into the game, all my progress was gone except the original dog that I picked. The same thing happened with my son. I love the cat game and had high hopes for this one. If you fix the bug, I'll gladly change my rating.", "Hi! I've been playing dog game for a few months now, but suddenly the app started closing on me and now after the loading screen it goes dark and won't open the game. I've Uninstalled it and reinstalled it, it connected to my account, and again the same problem. I'd contact support, but if I can't open the app I'm not sure how to contact support. Any idea why this is happening or how I can fix it? Thanks in advanced!", "Ever since the update I can't play the game. I LOVED playing it. The update has caused the game to no load. The start screen comes up, press the start button, says its loading to 55% then it just goes black and nothing else happens. I'm super upset because I love playing the game but now I'm also missing out on the events that are going on. Really hoping this gets fixed fast.", 'I play "Cat Game" as well this game is just as cute and is easy to play, however it\'s not as convenient as "Cat Game". I don\'t like the way hearts cannot be collected in one tap and expire too quickly. It takes up too much space on the club screen and messes with our club\'s ability to chat.', "900 dogs and no Index to keep track! ...... I started to play the game and it seemed okay .... Then, upon getting my first 'epic' dog I went to look for it but couldn't find it. I then realized that ALL dogs appear as the same level once opened. I searched for some type of index to differentiate the dogs but nothing. I informed the support team and they said there was no such option in the game. Absolute fail."]

title: WBYF: Dating For Dogs
description:
WBYF (Wanna Be Your Friend) is the official International dating app for dogs. Join us and be part of a happy dog family.
Start connecting with other dog-lovers in your or any location to match, chat - swap pet photos and go on dates. 

MAIN FEATURES
- Profile for your dog
- Meet dogs near you or around the world
- Private messages
- Vote for your favourite dogs
- Today's Birthdays list
- Find puppies and dogs for sale online
- View Lost and Found dogs
- See if anyone else has liked your profile
- Memory page of dogs (This page is "In memory of beloved pets who went to heaven")
- Go on dog dates

FREE TO USE
WBYF is free to download and use.

CREATE YOUR ACCOUNT
Creating an account is easy! Enter a full date of birth and sex of your dog, then start filling in some basic information to create your profile.
summary: Find friends for your dog around you or from around the world

title: Bumble: Dating App & Friends
description:
Welcome to Bumble üíõ The community with millions of people where you can find dates, make new friends, and meet people.

Bumble is a free dating app and social network for singles; the perfect place to meet new people, in an instant. Whether you want to find friends, make genuine matches, find meaningful connections, chat with strangers, make new friends, or even expand your professional and social network, we‚Äôve got you covered.

Changing the rules of dating

Bumble is a free dating app (to download and use) founded on respect, equality, and inclusion. You can find dates, meet up, and meet new people the way you've always done ‚Äî but on Bumble, women always make the first move. You won‚Äôt find that on any other dating apps. üïí With heterosexual matches, women have 24h to start a chat, and men have 24h to respond üí¨ Other matches (LGBTQIA+) have 24h to start a chat or reply before the match expires üë• Bumble comes in 3 modes to suit what you're looking for: Date, BFF, and Bizz

Discover our amazing features

Meet new people, make new friends, or find a great date using our free dating app. We‚Äôve levelled up from the days of dating sites, and now you have all these features at your fingertips: üëâ Unlimited Swipe: Meet new people by swiping left and right as much as you like üí¨ Unlimited chat so you can find the right matches üéµ Link your Spotify and Instagram account to share your interests with potential dates and friends üìπ Use Video Chat to get to know your matches better

Match with the right people

We're the first app to combine dating for singles, meeting new people, and making professional connections all in one app. We‚Äôre different from other dating apps, because we make it easy for you to connect. üìπUse Video Chat to get to know your matches better üì∑ Send your videos and favorite pictures while you are chatting with new friends üí§ With Snooze Mode, hide your profile whenever you want (you'll still keep all your matches!) üéµ Link your Spotify and Instagram account to share your interests with potential dates and friends

Boost your dating life with Bumble Premium

Bumble is a free dating app to download and use, and always will be! Our Premium features help you enhance your Bumble experience. üíõ See everyone who swiped right on you (your Beeline) üîÅ Rematch with expired connections for a second chance at a date üîÑ Extend your matches by 24 hours The buzz is real Bumble is much more than just a dating app for singles, or your average speed dating night. Join our like-minded dating community, meet new people, find your ideal partner or date. Here are our core values: üíõ We believe healthy relationships are fundamental to living a productive and positive life üíõ In the fight against old-fashioned hetero-norms, women always take the first step. üíõWe've changed the rules of the game to switch up the dynamics of dating üíõUnlike other dating apps, kindness is at the core of everything we do Inclusivity is key We‚Äôre committed to being totally inclusive, and supportive of our community whatever their gender, sexual orientation, or religion. Whether you‚Äôre looking for a place to find friends, a gay dating app, a bisexual dating app, a lesbian dating app, an LGBTQ dating app, a Christian dating app or a Jewish dating app; We‚Äôve got everything you‚Äôre looking for in our lovely community. --- Bumble is a dating app that is free to download and use. We also offer optional subscription packages (Bumble Boost and Bumble Premium) and non-subscription, single, and multi-use paid features (Bumble Spotlight and Bumble SuperSwipe). Your personal data is securely stored on Bumble - be sure to read our privacy policy and terms and conditions https://bumble.com/en/privacy https://bumble.com/en/terms Bumble Inc. is the parent company of Bumble, along with the dating apps Badoo and Fruitz. Enjoy all our dating apps!
summary: The dating app to meet new people, chat and date with singles or make friends!

comments: ["It is a total waste of time and money. It does not matter if you have premium, you won't be receiving any matches at all (I had subscribed to the premium, still the same). It's like a window shopping app where you just keep scrolling and scrolling until you're satisfied without hoping to get anything. For once I thought this app could be genuine and I purchased the premium, but no, if all I had to do was left and right swipe people, I might have as well stayed on Tinder for free.", 'The UI is quite user friendly. But few things which can be improved on. 1. Message notification doesn\'t pop up a lot of times 2. Call notification doesn\'t pop up ever, plus call drops multiple times 3. Filter option doesn\'t work properly, for example if I choose age range 33-36, I still see people of age 23 4. Algo for common interest can be improved specially for best bees feed, I get best bees who want "Something Casual" while my preference is "Relationship"', 'I can not escape the feeling of a jacked up algorithm. One that puts people on the bottom despite their subscription in some sort of "lead with a carrot" business model. That or no one\'s on this app, and the app does not seem to want to take people who have not been on the app in months in the algorithm. Furthermore, there seems to be no quick, obvious, and easy way to end your subscription.', "I used the app for about one year and had a few decent dates out of it. However, as soon as my paid membership expired, literally overnight, I went from having zero people interested in me to 47, of course being prompted to go back to the paid version. Didn't change location or filters during that time, so obviously, they are manipulating the truth and the end user.", 'For an app that requires access to your location, you\'d think they\'d give you an accurate mileage estimate for people near you, but nope they can\'t be bothered to do that. Just saw someone who lives in the next state over from me and, according to Bumble, they\'re 85 miles away from me. However, when I enter the city on Google maps, it gives me a much more accurate mileage: 156 miles. That\'s a 71 mile difference, nearly double Bumble\'s "estimate."', 'The worst of all dating apps. Like Tinder, gives you options from ridiculous distances, especially if youre in rural areas. Most people are visitors from very far. The worst part is once youve swiped left on a potential match they are removed from your likes and you probably will never see them again."you\'ve missed a potential match" forever. Also they put the location at the bottom so you have to scroll the whole profile just to see the distance factor. Overall a very bad experience', "This app is ok but needs work. I canceled my premium. One of the big thing that must be added is letting me know when the last time a person logged on. That way I'm not wasting time on someone who hasn't logged on in a month. That's a waste of a swipe especially a super swipe. Also need to separate straight people from gay. As I have swiped on the wrong person and they get all offended. If these things were fixed I would keep logging in.", "I have emailed support multiple times about transferring my premium subscription from a previously deleted account to my new account and there has been absolutely no response from anyone in support. Unlike other dating apps that allow you to re-instate previously purchased subscriptions without having to email support (that doesn't respond to you anyway), Bumble just really need to sort its issues out.", "Terrible app! you have to pay for basic Things like just to see who liked you you can only see the people that complimented your profile and that's limited, You have to pay for everything like super swipes & to go back if you made a mistake. They took down one of my photos for going against community guide lines but it's a picture of me in a long dress no nudity nothing inappropriate. & whatever preferences youre allowed to choose (age and distance) doesn't narrow down the field", "Still an awful app, I've tried it multiple times and men never see their related matches. We get search results from 97 miles away from people who don't match our criteria. And you can tell even from the blurry images that you never see the people who actually do swipe on you. It's entirely designed to keep you swiping without any actual results. Don't waste your time", 'Waste of time and money, the location of people is totally hit and miss, when you do "match" with someone it is debatable if they are actually real or generated by the app to keep you interested. For an app that is meant to compliment your social circle/find people with similar interests and so on, no one actually talks. Might just stick with the old-fashioned way!', "All the other dating apps I get plenty of matches, but bumble is awful at what it's supposed to do. No matches, and because of the time limit to message you often miss the matches you do get. Pointless app and a waste of time. Edited, after the reply I received more likes than before after I left a review, strange, then they started to get less and Ive just realised the compliment feature has been removed. I think the free compliments were the only thing that made bumble worth using.", "Because you can't filter results by important categories like religion without paying, the app is essentially useless. You are forced to weed through thousands of profiles that aren't close to your value specifications. The profiles layout is also a mess, listing interests in a buckshot-style jumble where things like children, religion, age, location, etc are thrown into the mix randomly and you have to look around more to find it (those should be at the top of the list).", "I think it's more likely to get struck by lightning and win the lottery at the same time than get a match. It's way too easy to accidentally swipe left, and those swiped on can't come back, and the highlights cost 8 bucks each. Like, who even? Fix your app.", "What's the use of having the dating interface if you can't even contact/connect to a prospect without having to pay a bloody fee? And even then, even if you do want to spend on it, the chances of getting catfished is unbelievably high. The aspect of this side of the app is completely useless. I will give it props if you're using it for business networking purposes and works well if that is your ONLY objective. The dating interface is bonkers.", "it's very picky and decisive wanting you to spend money just like any other app. they shouldn't just give the option free to connect with anyone but they should make a lot easier if you want to say hello or block or do what you would like explicit or not. there's filters for everything. just make it all around app that everybody can use. it's 2023 and this is the longest run on sentence I've ever done. but we all know what we're looking for in the beginning and in the end and who may b in middle", 'It\'s just as bad if not worse than Tinder surprisingly. Customer service is 0/10. I can\'t get a hold of any humans to discuss my problems, I\'ve sent at least 10 emails. I get photos randomly taken down because they "violate" community standards according to the algorithm. I\'ve purchased the lifetime membership twice and, like anyone, deleted and reinstalled the app many times, but now I dont have the lifetime membership, and they won\'t fix it. Summary: All dating apps suck.', 'Bait and switched into "subscription". If I wanted to continue after the 1 month trial I agreed to paid for, I would have chosen a less expensive package. I cancelled the subscription and contacted support 20 minutes after charged, I had to open a PayPal case. 2 weeks later Bumble hasnt responsed. Bait and switch auto-subscriptions are theft. Ive lost $60 to this "free" app and have zero dates to show for it, just "content sellers" posting their Instagram and onlyfans.', 'Totally wast of time & Money, I have not received positive responses from the opposite gender. The 30-minute spotlight feature, promising up to 10x matches, did not help. People seem less active, making it challenging to find potential matches. Considering trying other apps, Bumble has not been useful recently. I do not recommend it based on my recent experiences.', "Bumble is useless without a premium subscription. All filters except age & distance are now locked behind a paywall, so rooting through all the bad matches to find someone is a chore. You only get 24 hours to respond to a match, otherwise you have to pay to rematch. And if you accidentally swipe left on someone you do want to match with, you have to pay to undo it. If the woman matches but doesn't start chatting within 24 hours, (Something that happens A LOT) the match disappears completely.", "Not sure how I feel about it. So far I like how the verification process goes and the app runs smooth but been on it for 2 weeks with premium and not worth it. You don't really get as much people due to the fact that the premium is expensive and also the notification when you do get someone doesn't really appear on either the app notification or email. Also anyone you've liked you can't tell if they even seen the like. Definitely needs more work for the cost.", "I like this app, in my opinion it' s very nice but it's just ridiculously expensive. probably the most expensive app I've tried. so I subscribed in different app although I still use the free features on Bumble. Some things could be better. don't like the fact that only match girls can do first move, think that's silly. I've been on a date with a girl and she complained that men never say anything, then I said we can't, first move has to be from girl.", "When you pay to upgrade and it run out. I have found that when you get likes the system doesn't match you with them. I wants you to upgrade. They then timed out and their gone. Don't pay for the upgrade or you'll just have to delete your account like I did. It should be above all, about finding a connection.", 'Having a limit on likes per day isn\'t a bad idea, but this app\'s limit is almost cartoonish. I can\'t spend more than a few minutes per 24 hours swiping without being told I need to pay 3 WHOLE DOLLARS to keep going. It\'s asinine. On top of that, almost everything else is locked behind paywalls. Though I do like that you can list your pronouns without having to first pick "man or woman." But that\'s just basic decency, not a feature', "I've been on Bumble for a few weeks now. Ended up paying for the boost, matched with someone who, for their prompt, asked me to verify my photo. Prior to this I had tried probably 20 times to verify, and was never able to. Yes I tried photos with just myself. Mimicking the pose, hand gestures, and even location exactly, but couldn't verify. Now I'm stuck on the verification screen, I'm being ignored by the support team. 0/5", "To the pros: fairly clean & simple UI, tho a bit outdated. Cons: gps based search, meaning swiping endlessly tons of people in proximity, including tourists & people in the airport and there's no way to filter out. And you have to scroll all way down to find out person is living somewhere else or doesn't disclose. So looks like tinder at this point and more oriented towards finding one night stand nearby. Exhausting & very disappointing experience for me and after a long time trying it, I'm out", "So there is a subscription model for 21 dollars a month, but this subscription does not come with the ability to see who likes you. For that, you'd need ANOTHER subscription 13 dollars more expensive than the regular subscription. To unlock seeing who likes you, you have to pay 35 bucks a month. That's gotta be an accident, right? Why would this feature not be in the regular subscription?", "Don't buy the spot lights!!!! The app will self activate them and email support stopped trying to help! I tried just not being on for a couple days till subscription weekly one was added when I did log on it has already used it and times out! Yes I emailed them and they tried a couple time but stopped helping. Lost 5 so far. And they are not doing anything to help. Very disappointed in you guys. I'm done I've cancelled the subscription and not trying to get your help when you just blow it off.", "It's...ehhh. My issues are the inability to filter out poly/ENM profiles looking for unicorns, continuing to get likes from men when I am a lesbian, the constant message ads and empty notifications, and the high cost of premium. Been using it for a few months now, met one potential person but I'm demoralized. I won't renew my subscription.", 'I tried several times to get my picture verified, including taking a picture, posting it, and then without moving, taking the same picture in the verify area. They still said I could not be verified. I contacted customer service about it, and my app got stuck on the verify photo page and would not leave that page. I then contacted customer service two more times about it and still stuck. It would be nice to at least be able to try the app out.', "Well developed but core functionality is behind a paywall, and there's no incentive to pay for an app that feels dead. Honestly it looks great but actually seeing who has matched you is behind a pricy paywall, so it's a dice roll as to whether two people see each other, and this makes the limited ability to like people (an otherwise good feature) greatly lower the ceiling on chances of matching. People have moved onto other apps.", 'The app needs work on how it recognizes and interacts with phone media. It\'s difficult to get it to recognize videos & it has double standards when it comes to photos and videos. The app allows the most pixelated pictures you\'ll ever see; however, it won\'t let me upload perfectly fine videos due to "low quality" (they\'re not), wrong dimensions (huh?), or not being shot on my phone (really?). So far, it\'s not very user-friendly.', "Swear this app is a con. I have 9 so say 'matches waiting for me'. I just used a boost and spent the full 30 minutes swiping to see if I would get anywhere with any of them (get rid of or properly match with them) and I didn't come across a single one of these people. It is so blatantly a scam just to make people feel like they have no option but to pay to see more etc etc...", "The customer service for Bumble is absolutely terrible!! I have contacted them over 10 times in a two week span and Bumble has not replied to ANY of my inquiries. My account is stuck on photo verification and I cannot access any othet part of my account. I am currently paying for the Premium option as well. Don't use this app - they dont care about you at all.", "Bought premium (little under $9/wk because it was on sale). Was good at first but right now it's not letting me view profiles of people who have liked me (I can see their picture but when I click on them a blank square comes up instead of their profile). Literally the only reason I bought premium was so I could see people who liked me, so it's very frustrating that the feature stopped working. Hopefully it will work again soon. Edit: also not letting me send or view messages right now. :/", 'Very good idea but poor efficiency; is a pity that girls have only 24 hrs to establish a contact... Also, you should put more filters: for example: eyes color, hair color, etc., and stablish options to search by that criteria; for exemple, if I only want to meet people without kids or blonde girls or short (or tall) girls, be able to find those persons easily.', "The premium option is nice, maybe a little expensive for what you get. My issue is that with the premium subscription you run out of people within your filters. But if you're subscription ends you will run out of likes before you run out of people within your filters. Things don't add up properly.", "Even after having premium it doesn't let's text to someone who liked my profile. It clearly showed in best bees match. But it didn't let me text. What a pathetic app. They just want you to keep browsing and keep paying for super swipes or compliments even after buying premium. You will get nothing here. I think they just got some profiles when they launched the app. Might be no longer active because this app doesn't let people text even after liking from both sides.", "Don't recommend, I submitted seven verification photos exactly the way my profile poster was & when I tried to get customer support I've gotten zero response back other than them saying they verified who I am but to try to keep verifying my picture that matches. I paid for the week premium & the app is still stuck in the verification process & will not let me move forward. & they're still trying to charge me of subscription fee. The email I get back from customer service is a auto generated", "Horrible experience - they aren't responding to my emails to restore my lifetime premium membership. Been writing to them since two weeks to restore the unlimited premium subscription that I bought previously, no response to whatsoever, just an auto reply that we've received your email. The worst customer team ever. I don't even know if they'll fix this for me, but I'll continue to follow up."]

title: FeeDog - Raising Dog
description:
You can heal by feeding dogs and watching cute things!
Get a cute dog, Lucky, Rack, and various dogs!
When the dog grow up, they help Lucky fight ghosts together.
You can dress them in cute clothes, too!

# Good food is eaten automatically if you stay still.

# Bad food can be hit by touching the screen when it gets close.

# Attack ghosts with bad food!
- If you touch bad food, bad food flies to the ghost and damages it.
- If you feed good food, it will restore the ghost.

# The ghost attacks Lucky after a certain period of time.

# Raise Lucky's level in the store with the star coin you got after defeating the ghost.
- A stronger Lucky can hunt a stronger ghost.

# If you collected Gem, you can meet the dog through the dog basket!
- When you feeding milk to your dog , Lucky gets stronger, too!
- When the dog grows up, it can combine with Lucky and Rack to fight!
- Dress your dog in cute clothes!

# Game Tip!
- The more you keep the combo, the more star coins you get.
- Angel buffs cover up one mistake.


# FeeDog is requesting these permissions to store and load game data.

‚Ä¢ READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
‚Ä¢ WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE

FeeDog is a game without a server and does not use your information separately.

FeeDog web page: http://www.facebook.com/qssumstudio

comments: ["It's a very cute and fun game to play :). I love how we learn about how to treat real life dogs with the album descriptions, and I'd love to see more of that. The artstyle is very cute and the dogs are adorable! The gameplay is very fun and very chill, and I love the fusion feature. It'd be cool if we could get other dogs more easily, as well as a bigger variety of dogs. After you unlock Lack and reach level 100 with him there's not much left to do other than getting more stars to get more dogs.", "Its a pretty nice game, overall. Its got adorable graphics, and the tutorial is mostly understandable. It even teaches you a little about what dogs can and cannot eat ^.^ The gems can be hard, but are not impossible to get. Although, its hard to get a large sum without watching a lot of ads ~w~ Other than that, there isnt much to do. The 'walk' can get a little repetative, and I would like other things to do. Theres room for improvement, but its a nice game =3 a keeper for me", "This is one of the few games I can play without turning my wifi and data off due to ads. The few ads there are don't interrupt gameplay or make noise. The art style and little animations are very cute. There's an option to buy stars but it's still possible to get them in game (At least a hundred every day) and everything else can be earned in-game as well.", "This app is amazing - 11/10 would recommend. It's great; engaging and cute, with an amazing, simple, and easy to understand system that doesn't have the overbearing complexity that certain games do. It's great and relaxing, you get enough rewards and new things to really feel that you're accomplishing things, and it's fun - a rare but great find. Also, I love the way that you get gems, but the only thing I wish is that there was a way you could get more, even after you've watched the ads", "I have had this game on every device for years because you can play it offline. My no1 major issue is it forces you to replay the same 10 stages or so over and over again to grind for money so you can power up to move forward. Otherwise you'll eventually be forced to stop by an enemy you could not possibly defeat despite a perfect score on everything else. Wish there was an endless mode that didn't kick you from the game unless you messed up too many times.", 'This game is actually really helpful if you have ADHD and need to listen to informational videos or lectures but need to do something with your hands+visual stimulation as to not get bored or overwhelmed. Its just in depth enough where I can focus on what people are saying without thinking too hard about actions in game that I get distracted. Extremely useful for me personally!', "The ads don't interrupt gameplay, it's really fun and easy to learn how to play, and progress is at your own pace. I loved this game-- I first played it years ago, and got it again a few months ago for nostalgia. The new Halloween update annoys me, though. It's extremely buggy and made it nearly impossible to perform lucky hits.", 'this is a good game to play when your bored and need to pass the time! its a bonus that the chararacters and art style are adorable! there are a few things that i would like to suggest though. like a easier way to get rainbow stars and making the game have consistency of the controls actually working after a hour or so of playing. overall, the game is very fun and very adorable! ^^', "I've known this game for years, after I changed my phone four times. This is the cute and best game at that time, which can I finish after some time and now I've decided to re-install and start all over again. Though, I wish the dev could add more things and keep updating the game so I can enjoy it a little longer after finishing the main story.", "Could be improved, game speed is too fast to start with. The tips flash across the screen and nowhere else to read them. Instructions are too quick, no way to pause the instructions... Some features don't work right yet. But good idea, just needs some work. Very cute style.", 'A very simple but charming game! The dogs are adorable, and the gameplay, although very straightforward, is entertaining! I found myself completely in love with this game the second I opened it. No in your face ads, glitchy controls, or pixelated graphics. The art is adorable and the story is a little cherry on top of this amazing game.', "I love the art, and story. Its fun to discover new achievements, and just play in general. There is little to no ads which is a huge plus in my opinion and a really good time saver. So in all I would definately recommend this cute app to anyone who's looking for an easy easy way to kill time.", 'I like that the microtransactions are not as obnoxious as in other games. The in game currency is earned easily and quickly, watching ads is afaik entirely optional, but you earn currency by doing so. The transitions between power levels are smooth and earning gold for upgrades only turns more intense in later levels (ca. At 350 or so), but feels entirely appropriate.The graphics are adorable and the achievements (gold stars) are nicely integrated and unlock environmental interactions', "GReaT game! so cute and simple, great music, sounds and visuals. SO, CUte, great variation in dogs interactions and reactions! and i couldn't help but notice the great (i forgot word. as below)! it keeps from getting boring and monotinous by the varition in like everything, game speed, (great strategic introduction of lack). 6 stars for above and beyond! (ps. would like for there to be a toggle off for the red 'lucky' thing.?)", "So adorable and addicting. üòç Although I think it would be nice if it had more to the game than just feeding the dogs. Like maybe a neighborhood or something that you can walk around and collect and gain coins from feeding other people's dogs and playing fetch with the dogs or something. Just add something new, it might even be more addicting and adorable!!", "its one of the best games on my phone! super duper cute! its really a satisfying sound when the ghosts get hit. but there is one thing that kind of bugs me but only one thing I swear. why can't you get the rainbow star gems easier? I mean my poor puppy hasn't been able to level up forever! but I'm cool with that. oh and love the cool features like the comic strips and walking the dog!", "The game become very addictive when you get the hang of it, the art style is very cute. And the level up system is pretty simple too. But when you fully complete the game, it become boring and you're stuck in a loop where you just hit the bomb and eat the foods forever.", "To put it simply, BEST. GAME. EVER. Oh, where to start? It has dogs and puppies, it's VERY addicting and a great time killer when people like myself who don't have many things to do throughout the day can enjoyably play on their phone, it's graphics are great and simple, not to mention cute, the levels are still challenging even at level 200 and beyond (Like I said, I have a lot of free time and my only hobby is playing video games.) And even BEYOND what I just said, it's kept me coming back. :)", "I like this game, although I have a few issues with it. The upgrades get so expensive and pretty annoying. It's honestly a pain getting the rainbow stars to afford anything. I don't wanna spend an hour watching 25 ads for some of 'em, idk about you. I don't understand how to get the yellow stars either tbh. I wish there was some background on what the things you're fighting are, like why do they like dog food? And it has kind of bad wording at the start too. Other than that, it's pretty good.", "Really cute and lovely, a fun and addicting game! The only problem is that it gets boring over time if you are done with all story parts with both dogs and have all the puppies; there's nothing to achieve anymore. Being able to unlock more dogs to play with would be amazing.", "Very fun and enjoyable game. Whenever i need to add new apps to my phone this is one of my first ideas. It's educational teaching you about what figs and cats can and cannot eat. And the gameplay mechanics are simple but can become very challenging. All and all a great game.", "A very cute game, if you like dogs this is the game for you! The only reason I gave it a 4/5 stars is because you can't watch as many ads as you wish for, you can only watch a certain amount a day, and because you can get thigs out of ghe ads its very frustrating, at list for me.", "It's adorable and time consuming. The graphics are so cute and so is the music. The story, along with the concept, is so unique and portrayed in such simply effective ways. Completely recommend for people who have an appreciation for wacky and cute stories.", "It's a good game but what's the most annoying part about it is the hitboxes are wonky and it has a strange delayed lag to it which makes you have to tap the projectiles twice or they just completely ignore the fact you tapped them and end your game immediately. This has happened to me too many times and takes away from the relaxing cute aspect of the game.", "The game is actually a great time-killer. It's pretty straightforward, and you don't necessarily have to do purchases to win. I don't enjoy binging ads to get crystals, but at least they're not invasive of the gamespace. Overall, enjoyable experience.", "Adorable, some of the stuff is vague (I imagine it's just the language barrier) but it's easy to figure out. The rewards are fair and not near- impossible to obtain. A great, cute little game to play to pass the time.", "I loved this game so much!! I love the style, storyline, dogs, and pretty much everything about it! I did see some questions, though. The Touch Evade can be accomplished by tapping the dog repeatedly during walks (outside of levels). Although I love the game, it struck me as odd that you can't really seem to level up the puppies without milk. :)", "Its a really cute addictive game to play! Playing as two different dogs, both are extremely cute and have their own things to swipe at enemies. I'd highly recommend this game since its quick and easy to get behind, and fun to play to pass the time!", 'I remember playing this game when I was younger, it was and still is a lot of fun! The art style is adorable and the "album" is just the funniest. My only problem is that I\'ve noticed a few glitches when you go to "walk with the dog." Like with the red ball in the tree, it disappears halfway through the animation.', "Very simple but very cute game. If you're looking for something mechanically deep you'll have to look elsewhere but if you want a game with adorable visuals that you can play for a couple minutes without it demanding you give up months of your life, this is a great pick.", "Not too many ads, clean, silly, good graphics, honestly there isn't much to say. It's simple, and yet it never gets boring. Broken language from here and there, but it's translated. Totally reccomend :)", "It's a super cute little game with a repetitive yet good feeling mini game at it's core. I especially enjoy the art style and collection of events that can be occurred and catalouged. It also has no ads that directly stop your game and the placement of the sidebar ads have yet to be cumbersome", "Very fun game! I have played it on and off for the past 4ish years and am still not bored everytime I return. It weirdly isn't syncing up my achievements with my google play thing, but that might be an issue on my end. Over all I really appreciate the little snip bits of why the bad foods are bad for dogs. I think that's clever to add.", "Such a cute and adorable game. All of the dogs are cute and so are the animations. It's really smooth. One complaint I have is its too easy to collect coins. Another is it's too hard to collect stars. Stars let's you buy goodies like milk for puppies and more puppies. There's only two ways to collect stars: ads and walk the dog. Walk the dog is cute, but you barely get stars from it. I wish you could do more with it. Other than that, its a awesome game. So addicting.", "Very cute! I played this game like crazy a few years ago and went to revisit it, but I can't find an option to restore my progress. I made it really far and had a few different dogs, so I'm wondering if there might be a way to restore what I had? If not I'd be cool with just replaying, but if possible I'd love to get that back.", 'Really fun and cute, the graphics are simple and the gameplay itself is easy to understand. Also has interesting facts about dogs. Also the ads are not shown during actual gameplay only in the house or walking the dog.', "it's a really adorable and fun app. The animals are so cute and the game is really addicting! The only thing I would say is that you can only watch so many ads to get stars before it cuts you off for the day, and I don't think it's very necessary. It's not easy to get stars unless you watch the ads. But other than that, great app!", "A really lovely game. It's a simple time waster with a cute and well tied together aesthetic. The main gimmick is tapping the screen to bat away bad foods while letting the dog eat the good foods. The banner ads don't interfere with game play and ads can be watched for paid currency. You can get around $4 worth of currency per day through that and check in rewards without spending any money. Main negatives are poor English translations and a lack of explanations for other game mechanics.", "very cute! the game ain't hard to understand even if you miss what the tips says or notes that pop up, Which I do find they go away to fast for me to read but if it was big issue it's always a easy fix. The game style is adorable of corse. I like it and it's great!", "This is quite possibly one of the best (and cutest) games on the play store. After playing 400+ stages in only 5 days I can confirm that this game is just as addictive as it is cute. Although this game is originally in a different language the translation is well done and you barely see any ads. Even the premium currency is easy to get without spending a penny. I can't say anything bad about this game. l just wish there was a little more story. I can't wait to see more from the developers!"]

title: Dog whistle & training app
description:
EveryDoggy: all-in-one puppy & dog training app, created by certified canine experts. Built-in clicker for training sessions, fun tricks, essential commands, ultimate puppy FAQs and many more! All you need to socialize, train and make friends with your dog is now on one app.

You can train your dog using our built-in whistle.
Dog whistles emit a high frequency sound which is inaudible to humans but is loud for dogs. 
Dog whistle generates frequencies ranging from 22,000 Hz to 25,000 Hz.

Are you afraid that your lovely pet will chew on your favorite shoes or make your new carpet their toilet? With EveryDoggy you‚Äôll learn how to end and prevent any unwanted behaviors.

EveryDoggy's philosophy is based on three important Ps.
We are:
* Personalized. You'll discover a video training program that meets the goals you have for your pooch.
* Professional. Our certified pro-experts with many years of experience know how to teach every doggy.
* Practical. No excessive training theory, just practice‚Ä¶ a lot of practice!

What exactly does EveryDoggy have for you?

* Personalized Puppy & Adult dog training sessions
Do you want to help your pup to take his first steps at home or teach your dog some impressive tricks? Our step-by-step video courses will meet your needs exactly!

* Problem-solving guides
Having to deal with problems can really make you feel paralyzed and desperate. But don‚Äôt worry, we‚Äôve got your back! EveryDoggy provides effective solutions to behavioral problems. Learn to address leash pulling, house soiling, chewing, excessive barking, separation anxiety, unwanted jumping up, and more.

* Built-in clicker
A clicker is a great tool that can make positive reinforcement training more efficient. While training, use the clicker exactly when your dog performs the desired behavior and therefore, reinforce this behavior. You don‚Äôt have to purchase a clicker or a whistle as EveryDoggy already has these as built-in features.

* Positive reinforcement methods only
You love your dog. So do we! We use only positive reinforcement methods to make training fun and simple.

* Certified professional experts
All our content is created by certified dog trainers dedicated to your success.

Start training with EveryDoggy and live a happy life with your obedient and well-mannered pet!
summary: Puppy training app with dog clicker and whistle to raise an obedient pet
